00:17:48,792 --> 00:17:50,346
也是你的门生
and that he was your student.

169
00:17:50,513 --> 00:17:54,267
据说他特别敬重你
It's rumored he has a place in his heart for you.

170
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:59,981
图波列夫只会敬重他自己
There's little room in Tupolev's heart for anyone but Tupolev.

171
00:18:01,691 --> 00:18:04,944
会合后  两艘潜艇一起演习
Having made contact, we are to run a series of drills.

172
00:18:04,944 --> 00:18:08,197
图波列夫猎杀我们的潜艇
Tupolev will hunt us while we test our ship.

173
00:18:08,364 --> 00:18:12,326
我们测试履带式推进器
We are to evaluate the readiness of the caterpillar drive.

174
00:18:12,493 --> 00:18:17,415
然后在本月十六日返回波利尼湾
We return to Polijarny on or about the 16th of this month.

175
00:18:17,582 --> 00:18:20,147
舰长  这是一个历史时刻
Captain, This is an historic moment for all of us.

176
00:18:20,147 --> 00:18:22,712
我有一个请求
I should like to make a request.

177
00:18:22,878 --> 00:18:25,006
-在提出请求前...  -我知道这不合规矩
-Before you proceed...  -I know it's not protocol...

178
00:18:25,172 --> 00:18:27,528
但请让我
but would you permit me to...

179
00:18:27,528 --> 00:18:29,885
向船员公布任务
post our orders and inform the crew of our mission?

180
00:18:55,369 --> 00:18:59,290
我要去一个地方  你不能同行
Where I am going, you can not follow.

181
00:19:27,735 --> 00:19:30,571
彼得罗夫医生  立刻来舰长室
Dr Petrov, report to my cabin immediately.

182
00:19:30,571 --> 00:19:33,407
这里发生了意外
There's been a dreadful accident.

183
00:19:39,407 --> 00:19:44,207
4号码头  美军船坞  马里兰州

184
00:20:03,207 --> 00:20:05,207
接着!
Hey, buddy!

185
00:20:17,285 --> 00:20:21,455
下面没有支船架  快点动手
Listen to me. There's no cradle underneath it. Get it over。

186
00:20:21,622 --> 00:20:27,003
别那么固执  上来帮我吧
Relax! Stop being an old maid. You want to come up here and do it yourself?

187
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:34,218
瑞恩  谁让你进来的?
Ryan! Who let you in here?

188
00:20:34,385 --> 00:20:38,848
他们叫你来砌模型?
Have they got you playing with models now?

189
00:20:39,015 --> 00:20:44,729
该死的  叫他慢下来
Damn it, Phil! Tell them to slow down.

190
00:20:45,855 --> 00:20:50,318
这不是模型  这是深潜救助艇
It's not a model. It's a DSRV. Rescue sub.

191
00:20:50,484 --> 00:20:51,944
我知道这是什么  我原来见过一艘
I know what it is. And I just need to see one before.

192
00:20:51,944 --> 00:20:53,404
你拿它来做什么?
What are you doing with it?

193
00:20:53,571 --> 00:20:56,615
改装入坞设计
Ah, well, we're rigging it with a generic docking collar...

194
00:20:56,615 --> 00:20:59,660
它可以配合各国潜艇
so it'll mate with British, German... just about anybody's sub.

195
00:20:59,827 --> 00:21:03,122
在24小时内赶到世界每个角落
We can get it anywhere in the world in 24 hours.

196
00:21:04,707 --> 00:21:10,755
-你的背没事吧?  -没事  有没有时间?
-How's your back?  -It's fine. Have you got a minute?

197
00:21:12,506 --> 00:21:16,886
比常规的台风级潜艇更大  这些是什么门?
It's bigger than a regular Typhoon. What are these doors?

198
00:21:17,053 --> 00:21:19,805
你真细心
You don't miss much, do you?

199
00:21:19,972 --> 00:21:24,060
它们比鱼雷发射管大
Those are too big to be torpedo tubes.

200
00:21:24,227 --> 00:21:26,291
用来发射洲际弹道导弹?
Can you launch an ICBM horizontally?

201
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:28,356
是的  你想问什么?
Sure. Why would you want to?

202
00:21:28,522 --> 00:21:34,070
它们是对称的  排在舰轴两边
They're symmetrical, right down the long axis of the sub.

203
00:21:34,237 --> 00:21:36,906
拖曳线阵列声纳呢?
How about a towed sonar array?

204
00:21:36,906 --> 00:21:39,575
肯定不是  太靠近螺旋桨了
Nope. Too close to the screws.

205
00:21:39,742 --> 00:21:42,870
怎么会...
I'll be...

206
00:21:43,037 --> 00:21:45,957
这可能是履带
This could be a caterpillar.

207
00:21:46,123 --> 00:21:48,688
什么?
A what?

208
00:21:48,688 --> 00:21:51,254
履带驱动  磁性压水式推进器
Uh, a caterpillar drive. Magneto-hydrodynamic propulsion.

209
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:53,714
-明白吗?  -不明白
-Do you follow?  -No.

210
00:21:53,881 --> 00:21:58,344
它就像水中的喷射引擎
It's like a jet engine for the water.

211
00:21:58,511 --> 00:22:00,992
靠向后的反冲推进
Goes in the front, gets squirted out the back.

212
00:22:00,992 --> 00:22:03,474
没有运动部件  所以非常的安静
Only it's got no moving parts, so it's very, very quiet.

213
00:22:03,641 --> 00:22:06,206
有多安静?
Like how quiet?

214
00:22:06,206 --> 00:22:08,771
我们的声纳绝对发现不了它
It's doubtful our sonar would even pick it up.

215
00:22:08,938 --> 00:22:10,502
听起来像是鲸鱼游动
And if it did, it would sound like whales humping...

216
00:22:10,502 --> 00:22:12,066
或是地壳震动
or a seismic anomaly.

217
00:22:12,066 --> 00:22:15,194
一点也不像潜艇
Anything but a submarine.

218
00:22:15,361 --> 00:22:18,823
我们数年前研制这种潜艇
We messed with this a couple of years ago.

219
00:22:18,823 --> 00:22:22,285
但未成功
Couldn't make it work.

220
00:22:22,451 --> 00:22:24,300
他们成功了?
They really built this?

221
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,149
这不是个模型吧?
This isn't a mock-up or anything.

222
00:22:26,149 --> 00:22:27,999
它今早出海了
She put to sea this morning.

223
00:22:33,838 --> 00:22:38,426
十二岁时  我帮爸爸建造防空洞
When I was twelve, I helped my daddy build a bomb shelter in our basement...

224
00:22:38,593 --> 00:22:44,682
因为有人打算向佛罗里达州发射导弹
because some fool parked a dozen warheads 90 miles off the coast of Florida.

225
00:22:44,849 --> 00:22:49,145
这东西能向华盛顿和纽约  发射二百枚导弹
This thing could park 200 warheads off Washington or New York...

226
00:22:49,312 --> 00:22:55,484
而且神不知鬼不觉
and no one would know anything about it until it was all over.

227
00:23:05,161 --> 00:23:08,497
-舰长  你没事吧?  -没事
-Are you all right, Captain?  -Oh, yes.

228
00:23:08,664 --> 00:23:13,210
被地上的茶水滑了一跤  竟然断送生命
It's just to die for something as petty as slipping on tea.

229
00:23:13,377 --> 00:23:15,587
你不必自责  舰长  这是个意外
You're blaming yourself, Captain. It was an accident.

230
00:23:15,587 --> 00:23:17,798
回基地后你的心情自然会平复
You'll feel better when we put in.

231
00:23:17,965 --> 00:23:21,427
-平复?  -嗯  回基地后  舰长
-Put in?  -Well, to base, Captain.

232
00:23:21,594 --> 00:23:23,373
我们不能没有政治委员
We cannot go on without a political officer.

233
00:23:23,373 --> 00:23:25,552
医生  这是艘苏联战舰
Doctor, this is a combat vessel of the Soviet Navy.

234
00:23:25,652 --> 00:23:29,879
而我是个资深舰长
And I'm a senior combat officer.

235
00:23:29,879 --> 00:23:34,607
我们不能为这意外撤销任务
We do not cancel operations because of accidents.

236
00:23:34,774 --> 00:23:40,363
水兵  过来  过来
Seaman, come here. Come here.

237
00:23:41,364 --> 00:23:45,826
-你叫什么名字?  -副厨师洛吉诺夫
-Your name?  -Cook's Assistant, Loginov, sir.

238
00:23:45,993 --> 00:23:49,830
好  你和医生来当见证人
Good. I want you and the doctor to witness this.

239
00:23:49,997 --> 00:23:53,271
我要解除政治委员的导弹钥匙
I'm removing the Political Officer's missile key carry on...

240
00:23:53,271 --> 00:23:56,545
并由我来保管
and I'm keeping it by myself.

241
00:23:56,712 --> 00:24:00,383
舰长  我认为这得请示红旗舰队总司令
Captain, I think we should report this to Red Fleet Command.

242
00:24:00,549 --> 00:24:03,364
这恐怕不行  医生
I'm afraid that's impossible, Doctor.

243
00:24:03,364 --> 00:24:06,180
我们必须保持无线电静默
Our orders are for strict radio silence.

244
00:24:06,347 --> 00:24:11,561
-你可以走了  -这样不太好  舰长
-That's all, Loginov.  -This is most unnerving, Captain.

245
00:24:11,727 --> 00:24:15,585
发出两条钥匙
The reason for having two missile keys...

246
00:24:15,585 --> 00:24:19,443
就是为了避免...
is so that no one man may...

247
00:24:19,610 --> 00:24:24,782
-避免什么?  -避免一人控制导弹
-May what?  -May arm the missiles.

248
00:24:24,949 --> 00:24:27,159
也许我应该控制钥匙
Perhaps I should keep the key.

249
00:24:27,159 --> 00:24:29,370
谢谢你  医生  你可以走了
Thank you. That'll be all, Doctor.

250
00:24:29,537 --> 00:24:35,209
我将会发布指令  到时候你就会明白
When I address the crew, then you will understand.

251
00:24:38,546 --> 00:24:45,553
彼得罗夫  我不会向中央报告你的言论
Petrov, I will try to forget your comments when I present my report.

252
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:48,889
谢谢  舰长
Thank you, sir.

253
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:59,650
在方位310  速度12节  距离20000码
Holding steady on 310. 12 knots at about 20,000 yards.

254
00:24:59,817 --> 00:25:04,864
-有没有资料?  -电脑正在分析
-Have you got a make on it?  -The computer is chewing on it, sir.

255
00:25:04,931 --> 00:25:08,326
双螺旋桨  像是台风级潜艇
Twin screws. The plant noise sounds like a typhoon.

256
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:18,200
是艘新型潜艇  舰长
I'd say we got a new boat, sir.

257
00:25:18,419 --> 00:25:21,338
汤姆  最近几天总部有没有新消息?
Tommy, I miss something on the boards last few days?

258
00:25:21,338 --> 00:25:24,258
没有新的潜艇记录
Sub plant hasn't said anything about it.

259
00:25:27,094 --> 00:25:31,474
-电脑记录了多少台风级潜艇?  -6艘
-All right. How many Typhoons are listed?  -Six, sir.

260
00:25:31,641 --> 00:25:33,684
好的  称它为"台风七号"
OK. Call this guy Typhoon Seven.

261
00:25:33,684 --> 00:25:35,727
靠近点开始监听
Start a tape on him. See if we can work in a little closer.

262
00:25:35,727 --> 00:25:37,772
遵命  长官
Yes, sir.

263
00:25:39,357 --> 00:25:42,610
它会听到我们吗?
Won't he hear us?

264
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:45,863
潜艇有听觉盲点  博蒙特
Not if we stay in his baffles, Seaman Beaumont.

265
00:25:46,030 --> 00:25:49,992
他们听不见螺旋桨背后的声音
Come in behind his propeller and he's deaf as a post.

266
00:26:18,437 --> 00:26:21,669
声纳有新发现吗?
Any sonar contacts, Mr.Kamarov?

267
00:26:21,669 --> 00:26:24,902
没有新发现  舰长
No contacts, Captain. The sonar is clear.

268
00:26:25,069 --> 00:26:27,238
海面有没有发现船只  鲍罗丁?
Good. Do we have any surface contacts, Mr. Borodin?

269
00:26:27,238 --> 00:26:29,407
没有任何目标
No contacts, sir. Scope is clear.

270
00:26:29,574 --> 00:26:34,036
好  我要向船员说明任务
Good. Then it's time I explain our orders to the crew.

271
00:26:35,329 --> 00:26:38,499
同志们  我是舰长
Comrades, this is your captain.

272
00:26:38,666 --> 00:26:41,794
我感到很荣幸
It is an honor to speak to you today...

273
00:26:41,961 --> 00:26:44,484
我们驾驶祖国最先进的潜艇
and I'm honored to be sailing with you on the maiden voyage...

274
00:26:44,484 --> 00:26:47,008
作首次航行
of our motherland's most recent achievement.

275
00:26:47,174 --> 00:26:52,096
我们将再玩一个危险游戏
And once more, we play our dangerous game.

276
00:26:52,263 --> 00:26:58,060
跟我们的老对手美国海军  一较高下
A game of chess, against our old adversary the American Navy.

277
00:26:58,227 --> 00:27:01,835
四十年来  你们的父亲和兄长
For 40 years, your fathers before you...

278
00:27:01,835 --> 00:27:05,443
一直跟他们周旋
and your older brothers played this game and played it well.

279
00:27:05,610 --> 00:27:10,990
但现在情况转变了  我们占有优势
But today the game is different. We have the advantage.

280
00:27:11,157 --> 00:27:15,328
我想起我们昔日的人造地球卫星和尤里·加加林
It reminds me of the heady days of Sputnik and Yuri Gagarin.

281
00:27:15,494 --> 00:27:18,915
我们的火箭令世界震惊
when the world trembled at the sound of our rockets.

282
00:27:19,081 --> 00:27:22,585
我们的无声潜艇  也会令世界震惊
It will tremble again at the sound of our silence.

283
00:27:22,752 --> 00:27:26,839
-命令:以无声推进系统潜航  -是  舰长
The order is: Engage the silent drive.  -Aye, sir.

284
00:27:27,006 --> 00:27:30,843
-水柜控制  开启外门  -外门开启
Ballast control, open outer doors.  -Yes, open outer doors.

285
00:27:31,010 --> 00:27:34,305
潜水官  关闭主引擎  使用履带推进
Diving command. Engage caterpillar and secure main engines.

286
00:27:38,935 --> 00:27:41,020
正在开门  舰长
Doors opening, Captain.

287
00:27:41,187 --> 00:27:45,191
同志们  我们的舰队也不知道我们的威力
Comrades, our own fleet doesn't know our full potential.

288
00:27:45,358 --> 00:27:48,152
他们想尽一切办法测试我们
They will do everything possible to test us,

289
00:27:48,319 --> 00:27:50,884
他们最终只会自惭形秽
but they will only test their own embarrassment.

290
00:27:50,884 --> 00:27:53,449
我们将撇下其他舰只
We will leave our fleet behind.

291
00:27:53,616 --> 00:27:58,120
无声无息地穿过美国舰队的巡逻  穿过他们的声纳网
We will pass through the American patrols pass their sonar nets...

292
00:27:58,287 --> 00:28:03,417
进入各大城市  一边听美国摇滚乐
and lay off their largest city and listen to their rock 'n' roll...

293
00:28:03,584 --> 00:28:06,671
一边进行导弹演习
while we conduct missile drills.

294
00:28:08,923 --> 00:28:13,928
他们最终只会听到我们的笑声
When we are finished the only sound they will hear is our laughter.

295
00:28:14,095 --> 00:28:20,560
然后我们驶到哈瓦那迎接阳光和友谊
while we sail to Havana where the sun is warm and so is the comradeship.

296
00:28:21,852 --> 00:28:24,035
冷却系统已经启动
Cryogenic plant coming on line, Captain.

297
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:28,401
同志们  今天是大日子  我们缔造历史
A great day, comrades. We sail into history.

298
00:28:35,157 --> 00:28:38,619
启动履带式推进器
Caterpillar engaging.

299
00:28:39,704 --> 00:28:42,164
履带式推进器已启动  舰长
Caterpillar engaging, Captain.

300
00:28:56,762 --> 00:28:59,307
-发生了什么事?  -不知道
-What happened?  -I don't know.

301
00:29:26,208 --> 00:29:28,711
左满舵
Full rudder left.

302
00:29:28,878 --> 00:29:32,924
领航员  新航向: 250度
Navigator, new course: 250.

303
00:29:33,090 --> 00:29:36,302
好的  新航向: 250
Yes. New course: 250.

304
00:30:08,876 --> 00:30:13,130
声纳发现目标  左舷不远处
Sonar contact, Captain. Port quarter. Close aboard.

305
00:30:13,297 --> 00:30:17,510
-美国洛杉矶级潜艇  -美国潜艇! 舰长  我们...
-American, Los Angeles class.  -American! Captain, we...

306
00:30:17,677 --> 00:30:20,972
航向: 310
Course: 310.

307
00:30:21,138 --> 00:30:24,850
美军在跟踪我们?
Is the American turning to follow us?

308
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:28,563
不是  他们保持原来的航向
No, Captain. The American is continuing in his original course.

309
00:30:28,729 --> 00:30:32,984
-他们继续驶向西北方  -他们听不多我们
-He is continuing north-west.  -He can't hear us.

310
00:30:33,150 --> 00:30:36,487
会不会听见歌声?
And the singing?

311
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,295
让他们唱吧
Let them sing.

312
00:31:10,062 --> 00:31:12,043
你说什么? 检查仪器
What are you talking about? Check your gear.

313
00:31:12,043 --> 00:31:14,025
正在运行诊断程序  舰长
Running diagnostics now, Captain.

314
00:31:20,448 --> 00:31:23,993
声纳工作正常  苏联人消失了
The sonar is working, Captain. The Russian disappeared.

315
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:28,581
听到1分钟  位于坚守4000码外  然后就消失了
One minute he was steady, 4,000 yards off the bow then he was gone.

316
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:34,754
-我好像听到...  -听到什么?
-And for a second, I thought I heard...  -Heard what?

317
00:31:34,921 --> 00:31:39,258
我好像听到歌声
I thought I heard singing, sir.

318
00:31:39,425 --> 00:31:43,137
-歌声?  -是的
-Singing?  -Yes, sir.

319
00:31:44,837 --> 00:31:49,137
莫斯科  红旗舰队指挥部

320
00:31:54,523 --> 00:31:57,693
早上好  长官
Good morning, sir.

321
00:31:58,694 --> 00:32:01,739
早上好  长官
Good morning, sir.

322
00:32:03,616 --> 00:32:06,410
早上好  长官
Good morning, sir.

323
00:32:10,122 --> 00:32:14,502
早上好  长官  昨晚睡得好吗
Good morning, sir. I hope you had a lovely evening.

324
00:32:14,669 --> 00:32:18,047
今早有点冷
A little chilly this morning.

325
00:32:40,820 --> 00:32:45,575
马尔科·雷米斯寄了封信来
There's a letter from Marko Ramius.

326
00:32:45,741 --> 00:32:48,119
马尔科!
Ah, Marko!

327
00:33:19,358 --> 00:33:21,444
喂
Yes?

328
00:33:21,611 --> 00:33:25,281
我是瑞恩博士
No, this is Dr Ryan.

329
00:33:28,117 --> 00:33:31,495
-发生什么事了?  -不再是学术研究那么简单
-What the hell happened?  -This is no longer research project.

330
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:39,274
我找到了那些门的资料
I got a line on those doors.

