00:46:39,227 --> 00:46:41,632
身处险境
We're risking our lives here.

489
00:46:41,632 --> 00:46:44,038
普金会带来麻烦
Putin could have made complications.

490
00:46:44,205 --> 00:46:48,251
你以为他会袖手旁观  成全我们?
Did you think he would go away and sulk while we carried out our plans?

491
00:46:48,417 --> 00:46:51,712
他被谋杀?
Are you saying he was murdered?

492
00:46:51,712 --> 00:46:55,007
-老天  -别发牢骚
-My God.  -Stop whining, Yuri.

493
00:46:55,174 --> 00:46:59,053
他就是被谋杀的  他是个混蛋
So he was murdered. I have no problem with that. The man was a pig.

494
00:46:59,220 --> 00:47:03,391
-但我们应该一起做决定  -你不是指挥官
-But it is a decision we should have all made together.  -You are not in command here.

495
00:47:03,558 --> 00:47:08,604
如果真相败露  船员会叛变
If the crew finds out, we could have a mutiny.

496
00:47:08,771 --> 00:47:11,774
艇上每一件事都会影响我们
Everything that happens on this ship affects us all.

497
00:47:11,774 --> 00:47:14,777
纠察长已经起了疑心
The Master-At-Arms is already suspicious.

498
00:47:14,944 --> 00:47:20,575
-现在还可以回去...  -绝不能回头
-We could still go back.  -There'll be no going back.

499
00:47:20,741 --> 00:47:26,581
启航前  我给巴度宁上将寄了封信
Before we sailed, I dispatched a letter to Admiral Padorin...

500
00:47:26,747 --> 00:47:31,127
我在信内宣布了叛变计划
in which I announced our intention to defect.

501
00:47:32,878 --> 00:47:36,299
我的天  为什么?
In the name of God, why?

502
00:47:36,465 --> 00:47:41,137
到达新世界后  科特兹烧掉所有船
When he reached the new world, Cortez burned his ships.

503
00:47:41,304 --> 00:47:46,809
-手下只好跟他一起奋斗  -你把我们置之死地
-As a result, his men were well motivated.  -You have signed our death warrants.

504
00:47:46,976 --> 00:47:52,648
-巴多宁上将会派整支舰队来  -他们会追捕我们
-Padorin will send the entire fleet.  -Jesus! They'll find us.

505
00:47:52,815 --> 00:47:57,486
没有人会来找我们  住口吧
Nobody is going to find us. That's enough, Yuri.

506
00:47:57,653 --> 00:48:03,159
把潜艇交给美国是不够的
You had to do it, huh? You couldn't just turn the submarine over to the Americans.

507
00:48:03,326 --> 00:48:07,079
你还要发表政治宣言
You had to make a political statement.

508
00:48:07,246 --> 00:48:13,961
背后隐藏着什么心态? 为何不能静静地溜走?
Or was it something deeper, Captain? Something that made you unable to slip away?

509
00:48:14,128 --> 00:48:20,635
-是虚荣心作崇吧?  -我们为着不同的原因叛变  维克多
-Was it ego, Captain?  -We each have our reasons, Victor.

510
00:48:20,801 --> 00:48:25,431
收到这潜艇的蓝图后  我开始思变
My own began the day I was handed the blueprints for this ship.

511
00:48:25,598 --> 00:48:30,228
这潜艇本来只有一个用途  我改变它的用途...
A ship which had but one use. And as for the rest...

512
00:48:30,394 --> 00:48:34,941
我会负上全责
well, those are things that I alone must carry the burden for.

513
00:48:36,150 --> 00:48:41,739
安纳托利  你害怕我们的舰队  你应该害怕
Anatoly, you're afraid of our fleet. Well, you should be.

514
00:48:41,906 --> 00:48:47,078
我相信  我们有三分一的胜算
Personally, I give us... one chance in three.

515
00:48:50,414 --> 00:48:54,418
要茶吗?
More tea, anyone?

516
00:48:55,670 --> 00:48:58,506
不要了?
No?

517
00:48:58,673 --> 00:49:02,009
你们可以回岗位了
Then you may report back to your posts.

518
00:49:18,234 --> 00:49:21,821
听到舰长的命令吧  散会
You heard the captain, dismissed.

519
00:49:29,662 --> 00:49:31,747
舰长
Captain.

520
00:49:43,801 --> 00:49:49,473
我不会在他们面前反驳你
Captain, I would never disagree with you in front of the men, you know that.

521
00:49:49,640 --> 00:49:53,352
但这次维克多说得对
But in this case Victor was right.

522
00:49:53,519 --> 00:49:58,482
-不通知莫斯科会比较好  -瓦西里
-It would have been better if you had not informed to Moscow.  -Oh, Vasily.

523
00:49:58,649 --> 00:50:04,238
莫斯科不足为患  苏联海军也不难对付
Moscow is not the worry, nor the whole Soviet Navy.

524
00:50:04,405 --> 00:50:10,036
我了解他们的战略  我有优势
I know their tactics. I have the advantage.

525
00:50:12,747 --> 00:50:16,626
美国人才叫人担心
The worry is the Americans.

526
00:50:16,792 --> 00:50:22,089
遇上适当的对手才会成功
If we meet the right sort, this will work.

527
00:50:24,175 --> 00:50:28,804
如果对方性急鲁莽...
We get some buckaroo...

528
00:50:32,767 --> 00:50:37,563
有乱流  你不喜欢坐飞机?
Some turbulence. You don't like flying?

529
00:50:37,730 --> 00:50:41,943
这不算是什么  5个月前的乱流那才厉害
This is nothing. You should have been here five months ago.

530
00:50:42,109 --> 00:50:46,822
呕吐更是不在话下  我们在日本海遇上雹暴
Talk about puke! We ran into a hail storm over the Sea of Japan, Right?

531
00:50:46,989 --> 00:50:51,535
机师吐在挡风玻璃上
The pilot shot his lunch all over the windshield...

532
00:50:51,702 --> 00:50:54,372
我往无线电吐
and I barfed on the radio.

533
00:50:54,538 --> 00:50:57,520
一切倾囊而出
Knocked it out completely, and it wasn't that...

534
00:50:57,520 --> 00:51:00,503
那是次重量级呕吐
lightweight stuff either! It was that chunky, industrial-weight puke!

535
00:51:00,670 --> 00:51:04,090
要不要吃一点?
You want a bite?

536
00:51:04,257 --> 00:51:07,593
下次我会把你的高见记在备忘录中
Next time you get a bright idea, just put it in a memo.

537
00:51:10,593 --> 00:51:14,893
美国企业号  北大西洋舰队  新斯科舍以东

538
00:51:16,936 --> 00:51:21,607
-长官  -你可以走了  中尉
-Sir.  -That will be all, Lieutenant. Thank you.

539
00:51:21,774 --> 00:51:26,737
-鹰眼那班机怎么样了?  -遇上了强风
-That hawkeye from Weymouth Trap?  -Four wire. Caught a gust over the fantail.

540
00:51:26,904 --> 00:51:31,117
-那还不算太差  -这位先生想见你
-Not bad considering.  -The gentleman is here to see you.

541
00:51:31,284 --> 00:51:34,370
查理  你说什么?
The gentleman? What the hell are you talking about, Charlie?

542
00:51:34,537 --> 00:51:39,417
司令说  穿军服才不会惹人注意
I apologize for the uniform, sir. This is Admiral Greer's idea of a low profile.

543
00:51:39,584 --> 00:51:42,816
-你是司令的下属?  -是的  长官
-You work for Jim Greer?  -That's all right, sir.

544
00:51:42,816 --> 00:51:46,048
告诉我  到底发生了什么事
Then I imagine you'll tell me what all the hubbub's about.

545
00:51:48,926 --> 00:51:53,848
舰长  你有时间吗?  有个东西你应该去看看
Captain, you got a minute? Jonesy's got something I think you ought to see.

546
00:51:55,141 --> 00:52:00,396
-你去喝点咖啡  叫他们给我送茶来  -好的  舰长
-Martinez, get yourself a cup of coffee. Send me up some tea.  -Aye, Captain.

547
00:52:00,563 --> 00:52:03,858
舰长要一杯茶
Messenger, get the captain a cup of tea.

548
00:52:05,610 --> 00:52:13,200
台风七号消失后  我听到歌声...
Captain. Sir, the moment that sub went silent and I thought I heard singing...

549
00:52:13,367 --> 00:52:16,745
我听到很微弱的背景声
I heard something in the background, real faint.

550
00:52:16,745 --> 00:52:20,124
等其它潜艇离开后  我录下这些声音
After all those subs took off, I caught it again and got it on tape.

551
00:52:20,291 --> 00:52:25,254
用电脑过滤声带  剩下这声音
I washed it through the computer and was able to isolate this sound.

552
00:52:28,382 --> 00:52:33,429
电脑认为  这是"岩浆移位"的声音
The computer identified it as magma displacement.

553
00:52:33,596 --> 00:52:38,643
这套软件本来是用来探测地震的
The SAPS software was originally written to look for seismic events.

554
00:52:38,809 --> 00:52:42,647
所以  它用地震来解释陌生的音调
When it gets confused, it runs home to momma.

555
00:52:42,813 --> 00:52:45,816
-我不知道你想说什么  -对不起
-I'm not following you.  -Sir, I'm sorry.

556
00:52:45,983 --> 00:52:48,986
以十倍速度再听听
Listen to it at ten times speed.

557
00:52:56,577 --> 00:53:00,706
-这一定是人为的声音  -对
-Now, that's got to be manmade, Captain.  -All right.

558
00:53:03,084 --> 00:53:07,421
首次发现目标是9时15分  方位269
The first contact was at 09:15 and the bearing was 269.

559
00:53:07,588 --> 00:53:10,257
9时30分的时候  它在这里
At 09:30, it was here.

560
00:53:10,257 --> 00:53:12,927
在11时和11时15分又在这两点发现它
I came back to it at 11:00 and 11:15, here and here.

561
00:53:13,094 --> 00:53:15,951
苏联潜艇可以高速驶过
Remember the dispatch we got about Russian sub skippers running...

562
00:53:15,951 --> 00:53:18,808
雷克雅内斯海脊
the Reykjanes Ridge at high speeds...

563
00:53:18,975 --> 00:53:20,705
因为他们掌握了海底悬崖的地势
because they had hyper-accurate surveys of the underwater canyons...

564
00:53:20,705 --> 00:53:22,436
他们有"红航线一号"
Yeah, Red Route One.

565
00:53:22,603 --> 00:53:27,441
-海底悬崖的入口是托尔双峰  -是的
-The front door to those canyons was a formation called Thor's Twins, Right?

566
00:53:27,608 --> 00:53:29,944
看看这个
Look at that.

567
00:53:44,875 --> 00:53:47,587
-直驱"红航线一号"  -舰长
-Right into Red Route One.  -Captain.

568
00:53:47,753 --> 00:53:51,465
我可能疯了  但我打赌
You may think I'm crazy, but I'll bet that...

569
00:53:51,465 --> 00:53:55,177
这是艘新型苏联潜艇
magma displacement was actually some new Russian sub...

570
00:53:55,344 --> 00:53:59,432
它驶向冰岛海岸
and it's headed for the Iceland coast.

571
00:53:59,599 --> 00:54:02,873
恕我直言  钟斯
Have I got this straight, Jonesy?

572
00:54:02,873 --> 00:54:06,147
你不信任价值四千万的电脑说是地震
A $40 million computer tells you you're chasing an earthquake...

573
00:54:06,314 --> 00:54:11,652
你要另找答案
but you don't believe it. And you come up with this on your own.

574
00:54:11,819 --> 00:54:17,825
-是的  -别紧张  我相信你
-Yes, sir.  -Relax, you've sold me.

575
00:54:17,992 --> 00:54:25,708
汤米  计划航线  赶去"红航线一号"
Tommy, I want you to plot us a speed course for the bottom end of Red Route One.

576
00:54:25,875 --> 00:54:28,627
进了海底峡谷就无法找到他们
We'll never find him in those canyons.

577
00:54:28,627 --> 00:54:31,380
我们先移动到潜望镜深度  但最好先通知总部
First take us to periscope depth. But first we'd better phone in.

578
00:54:31,547 --> 00:54:34,675
遵命  舰长
Aye, aye, Captain.

579
00:54:42,433 --> 00:54:44,602
等等  钟斯
Hang on, Jonesy.

580
00:54:48,981 --> 00:54:53,069
如果我们能靠近它  你可以追踪它吗?
If I can get you close enough, can you track this sucker?

581
00:54:53,236 --> 00:54:59,450
是的  我听过它的声音  它逃不掉的
Yes, sir. Now that I know what to listen for... I'll bag him.

582
00:55:00,826 --> 00:55:04,413
-继续工作  -遵命  长官
-Carry on.  -Yes, sir.

583
00:55:04,580 --> 00:55:07,896
真是荒天下之大谬
That's the craziest notion I've ever heard...

584
00:55:07,896 --> 00:55:11,212
整艘潜艇全体成员都想叛变?
a serving line officer? An entire ballistic missile submarine?

585
00:55:11,379 --> 00:55:15,716
就算只是军官叛变  我也不相信
They can't all want to defect, even if it's only the officers.

586
00:55:15,883 --> 00:55:19,428
-他有什么计划?  -计划?
-What's his plan?  -His plan?

587
00:55:19,595 --> 00:55:23,057
苏联人连上厕所也会预先计划
Russians don't take a dump without a plan.

588
00:55:23,224 --> 00:55:25,559
高级军官
Senior captains don't start...

589
00:55:25,559 --> 00:55:27,895
不会贸然冒险
something this dangerous without having thought the matter through.

590
00:55:28,062 --> 00:55:30,400
-他将要做什么  直接驶往纽约?
-What's he going to do, he's just going to sail into New York?

591
00:55:30,462 --> 00:55:32,400
-可能就这么简单
-It might be that simple.

592
00:55:32,567 --> 00:55:35,444
在中情局纸上谈兵当然简单
Things may appear simple in the cubicle at CIA.

593
00:55:35,611 --> 00:55:40,825
在北大西洋面对整队苏联战舰  那就复杂了
But in the middle of the North Atlantic they get a bit more complex.

594
00:55:40,992 --> 00:55:44,620
-抽烟吗?  -不  谢谢
-Smoke?  -No, thank you.

595
00:55:44,787 --> 00:55:49,125
"海岸例行检查"是行不通的
And I don't think your notion of a few days inspection's going to wash either.

596
00:55:49,292 --> 00:55:51,502
我们必须要彻底研究整艘潜艇
In order to be any value, you'd have to tear it apart.

597
00:55:51,502 --> 00:55:53,713
这可能需要几个月
The metallurgy would take a couple of months.

598
00:55:53,880 --> 00:55:59,176
-那我们就扣押潜艇  -船员怎么处置？
-Then we have to keep it.  -What will you do with the crew?

599
00:55:59,343 --> 00:56:03,097
不愿叛变的人会回去告发我们
Ones that don't defect will go back and say we got the boat.

600
00:56:03,264 --> 00:56:09,312
-你打算杀了他们?  -我们不是在打仗
-Or do you plan to eliminate them?  -We're not at war, sir.

601
00:56:09,478 --> 00:56:13,192
我们要想办法不让他们知道
So you have to get them off the boat in such a way...

602
00:56:13,278 --> 00:56:15,192
我们得到了潜艇
that they think we don't have it.

603
00:56:15,359 --> 00:56:19,196
不能让苏联知道我们得到了潜艇
They'll go back and report that we don't have it to their bosses.

604
00:56:19,363 --> 00:56:24,535
否则说什么也没用  对吗?
Otherwise, this whole business is just academic, right?

605
00:56:24,702 --> 00:56:26,954
是  长官  我明白你的意思
Yes, sir. I think I see your point.

606
00:56:29,749 --> 00:56:34,503
-你上次睡觉是什么时候?  -很久之前了
-When was the last time you slept?  -A while.

607
00:56:35,922 --> 00:56:40,051
-外面的长官会为你打点一切  -谢谢你  长官
-The chief outside will fix you up.  -Thank you, sir.

608
00:56:40,218 --> 00:56:42,637
舰长
Captain.

609
00:56:46,641 --> 00:56:50,144
天快亮了  我们在战斗情报中心
It'll be dawn in a couple of hours. We'll be in the CIC.

610
00:56:50,311 --> 00:56:55,483
-我们要面对种种危机  -是的
-Things are liable to get a little dicey around here.  -Yes, sir.

611
00:57:04,659 --> 00:57:07,912
-你认为他疯了?  -疯得可以
-You think he's crazy?  -Certifiable.

612
00:57:08,079 --> 00:57:12,291
我不想见到他穿军服
And I don't care for him wearing the uniform.

613
00:57:12,458 --> 00:57:15,357
看到那戒指吗? 72年毕业  他是海军陆战队成员
Did you see that ring on his finger? The Academy class of '72. A Marine.

614
00:57:15,357 --> 00:57:18,256
不会吧...
You're kidding. How did you...

615
00:57:18,422 --> 00:57:25,304
格里尔告诉我  三年级时  他在直升机上遇上意外
Greer told me. Summer of his third year, he went down in a chopper accident.

616
00:57:25,471 --> 00:57:28,891
很惨  机师和队员都死了
Bad. Pilot and crew killed.

617
00:57:28,891 --> 00:57:32,311
他花了十个月接受牵引治疗  花了一年学走路
That kid spent 10 months in traction and another year learning to walk again.

618
00:57:33,688 --> 00:57:37,525
第四年  是在医院念的
He did his fourth year from the hospital.

619
00:57:37,692 --> 00:57:43,155
你可以考虑给他一次机会
It's up to you, Charlie, but you might consider cutting him a little slack.

620
00:57:45,241 --> 00:57:49,829
反正苏联人会先找到那潜艇
The Russians will find that sub before we get near it anyway.

621
00:58:10,725 --> 00:58:15,104
-正在穿越托尔双峰  -很好
-Passing Thor's Twins, sir.  -Very good.

622
00:58:19,483 --> 00:58:23,779
-穿越托尔双峰  -很好  开始进入航道
-Passing the Twins now, Captain.  -Very good. Commence your run.

623
00:58:23,946 --> 00:58:27,158
-拐弯时通知我  -好的  舰长
-Call me when you get to the first turn.  -Aye, Captain.

624
00:58:27,325 --> 00:58:31,370
-卡马洛夫  开始进入航道  -遵命  长官
Mr. Kamarov, you may commence your run now.  -Aye, sir.

625
00:58:31,537 --> 00:58:37,877
开始第一阶段  航向: 260  速度: 18节
First leg on my mark. Course: 260. Speed: 18 knots.

626
00:58:38,044 --> 00:58:40,796
深度: 270米
Depth: 270 meters.

627
00:58:40,963 --> 00:58:46,177
五  四  三  二  一
Five, four, three, two, one...

628
00:58:46,344 --> 00:58:48,638
开始
Mark.

629
00:58:48,804 --> 00:58:54,602
下潜命令  航向: 260  速度: 18节
Diving Command, course: 260. Speed: 18 knots.

630
00:58:54,769 --> 00:59:01,525
给我秒表和地图  我能驾驶没有窗的飞机
Give me a stopwatch and a map and I'll fly the Alps in a plane with no windows.

631
00:59:01,692 --> 00:59:05,112
如果地图够准确的话
If the map is accurate enough.

632
00:59:25,299 --> 00:59:29,387
我们进了航道  接近首个弯口
We're in the lane and approaching the first turn.

633
00:59:29,554 --> 00:59:34,475
三十秒后左转到方位195
Come left to course 195 in 30 seconds.

634
00:59:34,642 --> 00:59:39,564
上升到200米  保持速度
Decrease depth to 200 meters. Maintain speed.

635
00:59:41,774 --> 00:59:45,861
舰长  我们正在接近首个弯口  25秒后转到方位195
Captain, we are approaching the first turn. 25 seconds to course 1-9-5.

636
00:59:46,028 --> 00:59:50,825
加速至26节  重新计算
Increase speed to 26 knots and recompute.

637
00:59:52,994 --> 00:59:55,913
遵命  舰长
Aye, Captain.

638
00:59:56,080 --> 01:00:00,001
领航员  以26节的速度重新计算
Navigator, recompute for 26 knots.

639
01:00:00,167 --> 01:00:05,464
准备拐弯  五  四  三...
Turn on my mark. Five, four, three...

640
01:00:05,631 --> 01:00:08,509
二  一  开始
two, one, mark.

641
01:00:08,676 --> 01:00:13,472
左转到方位195  提升舰首
Diving control, come left to 195. Up on the bow planes.

642
01:00:21,397 --> 01:00:26,903
航向195  保持时速26节
Course now 195 and maintaining speed 26 knots.

643
01:00:31,198 --> 01:00:35,286
-卡马洛夫先生?  -下一阶段
-Mr. Kamarov?  -Next leg, Captain.

644
01:00:35,453 --> 01:00:41,125
八分四十秒后  右转到方位240
Come right to 240 at 8 minutes and 40 seconds.

645
01:00:41,292 --> 01:00:45,087
很好  保持航线和速度
Very good. Maintain course and speed.

646
01:00:48,007 --> 01:00:51,594
太快了  瓦西里
Too fast, Vassily. Too fast.

647
01:00:51,761 --> 01:00:57,183
该用什么速度  图表写得很清楚
Those charts are laid out precisely. So many knots for so many seconds.

648
01:00:57,350 --> 01:01:02,480
-这艘船会捱不住的  -说话小心点  斯莱文先生
-This thing handles like a pig.  -Watch your bearing, Mr. Slavin.

649
01:01:08,444 --> 01:01:12,365
十五秒后转向  要减速吗?
15 seconds to turn, Captain. Should we decrease speed?

650
01:01:12,531 --> 01:01:16,619
不  准备右转
Negative. Prepare to come right.

651
01:01:16,786 --> 01:01:21,499
八  七  六  五  四...
Eight, seven, six, five, four...

652
01:01:21,666 --> 01:01:25,419
三  二  一  开始
three, two, one, mark.

653
01:01:25,586 --> 01:01:31,217
舰首俯倾15度  右转到240  快
15 degrees down angle on the bow planes. Come right 240. Move it!

654
01:01:50,736 --> 01:01:55,783
我们位置正确  下一阶段  34分钟后  抵达海王山丘
We're in the lane. Next leg 34 minutes to the Neptune Massif.

655
01:01:55,950 --> 01:01:58,953
航向: 240
Course: 240.

656
01:02:11,132 --> 01:02:14,844
-发生什么事?  -冷却系统故障
-What happened?  -The cryogenic plant.

657
01:02:15,011 --> 01:02:20,141
磁石无法降温  履带温度高出了50度
The magnets aren't being cooled. We're 50 degrees above red line.

658
01:02:20,308 --> 01:02:25,146
-如果不关掉它  它会熔化  -关掉它吧
-It's going to melt.  -Kill it, shut it down!

659
01:02:28,816 --> 01:02:32,069
-舰长  -发生了什么事?
-Captain?  -What happened?

660
01:02:32,069 --> 01:02:35,323
-冷却系统故障  -反应堆有损坏吗?
-The cryogenic plant failed.  -Reactor damage?

661
01:02:35,489 --> 01:02:40,077
-反应堆自动急停  -核心是否有损坏?
-The reactor scrammed automatically.  -Was there any core damage?

662
01:02:40,244 --> 01:02:43,623
-有没有辐射泄漏  -暂时还不知道
-Any radiation leakage?  -I don't know yet.

663
01:02:43,789 --> 01:02:50,046
-修复需要多长时间?  -先要找出原因
-How long will it take to fix?  -I've got to find out what's wrong first.

664
01:02:51,631 --> 01:02:55,551
舰长  我们必须停下来  修理履带系统
Captain, we will have to stop until we can repair the caterpillar unit.

665
01:02:55,718 --> 01:03:02,058
-那就用普通推进系统航行  -舰长  我们会发出声音
-Negative. We will run on normal propulsion.  -Captain, we will not be silent.

666
01:03:02,225 --> 01:03:08,022
时速改为20节  启动螺旋桨
Make revolutions for 20 knots and engage the propellers.

667
01:03:10,524 --> 01:03:16,822
-是  舰长  -他会把我们害死
-Aye, Captain.  -That man will get us all killed.

668
01:03:21,244 --> 01:03:24,580
舰长自有分寸
The captain knows what he's doing.

669
01:03:28,125 --> 01:03:32,505
海军行动? 我不了解这些事
Naval activities? I have no knowledge of this.

670
01:03:32,672 --> 01:03:36,801
-我没当过海员  -大使先生
-But then, I never was a sailor.  -Mr. Ambassador...

671
01:03:36,968 --> 01:03:41,847
贵国在北大西洋  有一百艘军舰
You have nearly 100 naval vessels operating in the North Atlantic right now.

672
01:03:42,014 --> 01:03:45,184
贵国的战机  抛下无数声纳浮标
Your aircraft have dropped enough sonar buoys

673
01:03:45,351 --> 01:03:48,020
你可以踏着浮标  从格陵兰走到苏格兰
that a man could walk from Greenland to Scotland without getting his feet wet.

674
01:03:48,020 --> 01:03:50,690
我们要试一下吗?
Shall we dispense with the bull?

675
01:03:50,856 --> 01:03:55,987
你的表达总是很有技巧
You make your point as delicately as ever, Mr. Pelt. But...

676
01:03:56,153 --> 01:04:01,033
军事演习可能是战争的前奏
And what looks like an exercise could be a prelude to war.

677
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:03,723
你怎能分辨虚实?
How can we tell the difference?

678
01:04:03,723 --> 01:04:06,247
我们必须派船去监视你们
Prudence demands that we deploy ships to observe yours.

679
01:04:06,414 --> 01:04:09,417
你的政府可能会起了戒心...
Your government should consider that...

680
01:04:09,584 --> 01:04:15,381
双方的船舰和战机太过接近
that having your ships and ours in such proximity...

681
01:04:15,548 --> 01:04:21,637
本来就危险  战争就是这样
is inherently dangerous? Wars have begun that way, Mr. Ambassador.

682
01:04:31,147 --> 01:04:33,482
我们遗失了一艘潜艇
We have lost one of our submarines.

683
01:04:33,482 --> 01:04:35,818
-遗失?  -它可能沉没了...
-Lost it?  -We fear she may be down, and...

684
01:04:35,985 --> 01:04:39,071
说起来很尴尬
this is most embarrassing, but...

685
01:04:39,238 --> 01:04:45,786
船上的军官  都是高干子弟
Several of the crew, the officers, are sons of high Party officials.

686
01:04:45,953 --> 01:04:51,709
其中一位甚至是中央委员的儿子
One is even the son of a Central Committee member. I can't say which.

687
01:04:53,002 --> 01:04:58,049
-你们正在进行拯救行动?  -是的
-You're telling me this is a massive rescue operation?  -That is correct.

688
01:05:01,135 --> 01:05:04,722
真遗憾  需要我们帮忙吗?
I'm terribly sorry. How can we help?

689
01:05:07,058 --> 01:05:11,646
-我觉得...  -进行联合援救?
-I'm not sure that...  -Perhaps a joint rescue mission?

690
01:05:14,982 --> 01:05:18,027
非常感谢
That is very gracious of you, sir.

691
01:05:18,194 --> 01:05:21,155
我会传达你的好意
I will pass your offer on.

692
01:05:21,322 --> 01:05:24,533
但这次  我们暂时不需要帮忙
But at this time, I think we're doing everything that can be done.

693
01:05:28,233 --> 01:05:33,833
熊狐步号  苏联反潜战机  冰岛以南

694
01:05:44,345 --> 01:05:46,639
舰长
Captain.

695
01:05:48,849 --> 01:05:54,730
我们根据你的意思制定战略  舰队会找到我们
Our strategy depends on your answer. The entire fleet will know where we are.

696
01:05:54,897 --> 01:05:59,819
舰长  声纳在低空发现一架多引擎螺旋桨飞机
Captain, Sonar. We have just been overflown by a multi-engine turboprop.

697
01:05:59,986 --> 01:06:02,697
启动传声器
Put it on audio.

698
01:06:05,199 --> 01:06:10,496
正在接近  水面有小物件
Short transients, close aboard. Water entry of small objects.

699
01:06:10,663 --> 01:06:14,750
-声纳浮标  -战斗岗位
-Sonar buoys.  -Battle stations.

700
01:06:14,917 --> 01:06:18,004
战斗岗位!
Battle stations!

701
01:06:18,170 --> 01:06:21,799
还有多久到达海王山丘?
How long to Neptune Massif?

702
01:06:21,966 --> 01:06:26,596
-多久?  -4分10秒
-How long?  -4 minutes, 10 seconds.

703
01:06:26,762 --> 01:06:30,808
-要下潜吗?  -太迟了
-Should we bottom the boat, Captain?  -No. Too late for that now.

704
01:06:30,975 --> 01:06:36,731
没时间了  计算参数  准备鱼雷散射
We're out of time. Counter measures. Prepare to launch a full spread.

705
01:06:45,239 --> 01:06:48,367
这里是计算机导航  请求发射许可
Aircraft on computer guidance. Request permission to launch the weapon.

706
01:06:48,534 --> 01:06:51,454
允许发射
You are authorized to launch the weapon.

707
01:06:53,623 --> 01:06:55,917
鱼雷发射
Weapon is away.

708
01:06:59,587 --> 01:07:04,133
-高速螺旋桨  水里有鱼雷  -密切注视
-High-speed screw. Torpedo in the water. -Stand by.

709
01:07:05,843 --> 01:07:09,430
是实弹鱼雷
Torpedo is active.

710
01:07:09,597 --> 01:07:13,517
-鱼雷已经锁定目标  -发射反鱼雷
-Torpedo has acquired.  -Launch counter measures.

711
01:07:13,684 --> 01:07:16,354
发射反鱼雷  遵命  长官
Launch countermeasures. Aye, sir.

712
01:07:21,609 --> 01:07:24,132
我们在正确的航线上
We're in the lane.

713
01:07:24,132 --> 01:07:26,656
-何时到达下一个弯角?  -2分9秒
-How long to the turn at Massif?  -2 minutes, 9 seconds.

714
01:07:26,822 --> 01:07:30,159
我们没有空间进行机动
We have no room to maneuver in these canyons, Captain.

715
01:07:30,326 --> 01:07:32,787
闭嘴
Shut up!

716
01:07:36,707 --> 01:07:39,689
鱼雷接近反鱼雷  失去目标
Torpedo has reached counter measures. Torpedo has lost contact.

717
01:07:39,689 --> 01:07:42,672
接近山丘
Massif approaching.

718
01:07:45,341 --> 01:07:51,264
鱼雷再次锁定目标
Torpedo has reacquired and is homing.

719
01:07:51,430 --> 01:07:56,894
-报告情况  -30秒后在山丘拐弯
-Give me the count.  -Turn at Massif 40 degrees starboard in 30 seconds.

720
01:07:57,061 --> 01:08:00,815
-鱼雷命中时间?  -35秒
-Time to torpedo impact?  -Torpedo impact, 35 seconds.

721
01:08:00,982 --> 01:08:04,735
-超速前进  -超速前进
-Increase to flank.  -Full ahead flank.

722
01:08:06,195 --> 01:08:11,701
鱼雷40秒  35秒后命中目标
Torpedo impact now 40 seconds. 35 seconds.

723
01:08:19,166 --> 01:08:21,961
30秒
30 seconds.

724
01:08:22,128 --> 01:08:26,299
接近山丘弯角  七  六...
Turn at Massif in seven, six...

725
01:08:26,465 --> 01:08:29,719
五  四...
five, four...

726
01:08:29,886 --> 01:08:33,973
三  二  一  开始
three, two, one, mark.

727
01:08:34,140 --> 01:08:36,162
鱼雷25秒后命中
Torpedo impact: 25 seconds.

728
01:08:36,162 --> 01:08:38,185
-舰长  要转向了  -等一会儿
-The turn, Captain.  -Not yet.

729
01:08:41,480 --> 01:08:45,776
延迟了八秒  九秒  十秒
Mark plus eight seconds, nine, ten...

730
01:08:45,943 --> 01:08:52,909
11秒  12  13  14...  延迟15秒
11 seconds, 12, 13, 14... plus 15 seconds.

731
01:08:53,075 --> 01:08:55,828
舰长  我们严重偏离正常位置
Captain, we're out of position so much by a boat length.

732
01:08:55,828 --> 01:08:58,581
鱼雷15秒后命中
Torpedo impact now in 15 seconds.

733
01:08:58,748 --> 01:09:02,001
发出警告
Sound collision.

734
01:09:02,168 --> 01:09:04,420
-我们偏离了航线  -你退下岗位
-Captain, we're out of the lane.  -You're relieved.

735
01:09:04,420 --> 01:09:06,672
鲍罗丁
Borodin?

736
01:09:12,386 --> 01:09:17,892
右满舵  右引擎反转
Right full rudder! Reverse starboard engine!

737
01:09:21,854 --> 01:09:25,024
鱼雷命中时间: 12秒
Torpedo impact: 12 seconds.

738
01:09:25,191 --> 01:09:31,614
10, 9, 8, 7, 6, 5...

739
01:09:34,659 --> 01:09:39,455
-领航员  报告度数  -偏离了十六度
-Navigator.  -16 degrees off the bow plane.

740
01:10:02,395 --> 01:10:07,900
-他们向我们开火!  -冷静点  小伙子
-Captain, they're really shooting at us! Why?  -Easy, boy.

741
01:10:08,067 --> 01:10:13,032
如果他们真的开火  我们早就死了
If they were really shooting at us, we'd be dead by now.

742
01:10:32,474 --> 01:10:36,770
我知道履带出了什么问题
I found out what happened to the caterpillar.

743
01:10:36,937 --> 01:10:40,148
缓冲器被破坏
The buffer circuit has been torn out.

744
01:10:40,148 --> 01:10:43,360
履带迟早会负荷过重
It was only a matter of time, before an overload shut it down.

745
01:10:43,527 --> 01:10:47,009
你说什么?
What are you saying?

746
01:10:47,009 --> 01:10:50,492
有人知道如何弄坏履带而不被轻易发现
Whoever did this knew how to cripple the caterpillar in a way not easy to find.

747
01:10:50,659 --> 01:10:53,996
艇上有内奸
Captain, we have a saboteur on board.

748
01:10:58,083 --> 01:11:02,003
不会是军官  军官不会等到启航后才动手
It can't be any of the officers, They had plenty of time before we embarked.

749
01:11:02,003 --> 01:11:05,924
这一定是水兵干的
Must be a member on the crew.

750
01:11:06,091 --> 01:11:11,138
翻查普金的档案  调查海员身分
Go to Putin's cabin. Check his files for information on the crew.

751
01:11:11,305 --> 01:11:13,640
我们可能要提早遣散水兵
We may have to put them off before we planned.

752
01:11:16,226 --> 01:11:20,897
"苏联人连上厕所  也会预先计划"
"Your average Russkie don't take a dump without a plan."

753
01:11:22,649 --> 01:11:25,402
等等
And wait a minute.

754
01:11:25,569 --> 01:11:30,699
他已经有办法赶走船员了
We don't have to get the crew off the sub. He would have had to do that.

755
01:11:30,866 --> 01:11:34,745
我们只需猜想他下一步要干什么
We just have to figure out what he's going to do.

756
01:11:34,745 --> 01:11:38,624
如何赶走艇员
How is he going to get them off the sub?

757
01:11:39,958 --> 01:11:43,086
船员要有离艇的意图
They'd have to want to get off.

758
01:11:44,296 --> 01:11:49,134
船员为什么想离开潜艇?
How do you get a crew to want to get off a submarine?

759
01:11:49,301 --> 01:11:53,388
船员为什么想离开核潜艇...
How do you get a crew to want to get off a nuclear sub...

760
01:11:53,555 --> 01:11:57,601
-我知道他会怎样赶走船员  -我很忙  杰克
-I know how he'll get the crew off.  -Not now, Jack.

761
01:11:57,768 --> 01:12:04,441
扬基一号进入紧急状态
Yankee One, declaring an emergency.

762
01:12:04,608 --> 01:12:10,447
扬基一号  方位270  速度低速  完毕
Yankee One, vector 270. Speed is buster, over.

763
01:12:10,614 --> 01:12:13,075
扬基一号  再说一遍
Say again, Yankee One.

764
01:12:13,241 --> 01:12:15,952
熊狐步号太接近部队
A Bear Foxtrot got too close to the group.

765
01:12:15,952 --> 01:12:18,664
它和一架F14战机相撞
One of the F-14s crowded him, and they bumped.

766
01:12:18,830 --> 01:12:24,294
战机损伤  他们引导它返回母舰
He's losing hydraulic fluid. They're trying to get him back aboard now.

767
01:12:24,461 --> 01:12:27,255
-忙碌的早晨  -嗯
-Busy morning.  -Mmm.

768
01:12:27,422 --> 01:12:32,970
昨晚苏联战舰在东边港口戒备
During the night, Russian attack subs are now stationed off every East Coast port.

769
01:12:33,136 --> 01:12:35,639
我们在这里
We're up here.

770
01:12:35,806 --> 01:12:39,059
新泽西舰队赶到海岸
The New Jersey is moving up the coast...

771
01:12:39,226 --> 01:12:42,145
苏军出动攻击型潜艇
while the Russians, aside from over 100 bear foxtrots, have a row of subs...

772
01:12:42,145 --> 01:12:45,065
和海面舰队
and several surface groups.

773
01:12:45,232 --> 01:12:48,610
-火力强大  -对于一支救援队的话  是的
-That's a lot of firepower.  -For a rescue team, yes.

774
01:12:48,777 --> 01:12:50,403
还有一件怪事
And there's something else strange.

775
01:12:50,403 --> 01:12:52,030
他们不关心声纳探测结果
They're using sonar as if they're looking for something, but nobody's listening.

776
01:12:52,030 --> 01:12:55,284
什么意思?
What do you mean?

777
01:12:55,450 --> 01:12:57,831
以30节的速度航行
At their speed of 30 knots,

778
01:12:57,850 --> 01:13:00,831
他们的声音大过我女儿的音响  居然听不到
they could run over my daughter's stereo and not hear it.

779
01:13:02,291 --> 01:13:05,337
-他们不是寻找雷米斯  他们驱赶他
-They're not trying to find Ramius, they're trying to drive him.

780
01:13:05,341 --> 01:13:07,337
-驱赶他到哪里?
-Drive him where?

781
01:13:10,090 --> 01:13:12,926
赶到敌人的地盘
Hounds to the hunters.

782
01:13:13,093 --> 01:13:17,514
这舰长的确会去美国
Your sub captain is going to make it to America, Mr. Ryan.

783
01:13:17,681 --> 01:13:20,851
他将会在抵岸前身亡
He's going to die within sight of it.

784
01:13:21,018 --> 01:13:25,731
他的僚机要求准许发炮
His wing man kept requesting permission to fire.

785
01:13:25,897 --> 01:13:31,069
若有人轻举妄动  我们会卷入大战
omebody messes up, we'll be in the biggest naval battle since the Jutland. Jesus!

786
01:13:31,236 --> 01:13:36,199
-水温太低  不能弹射  -尝试登上甲板
-The water's too cold to eject.  -Air boss will try to bring him aboard.

787
01:13:36,366 --> 01:13:40,495
-这是什么潜艇?  -巴特·曼库索的潜艇
-Excuse me, sir. What's this sub off by herself?  -Bart Mancuso's boat.

788
01:13:40,662 --> 01:13:43,957
他正赶去红航线一号
He's going to the bottom of Red Route One.

789
01:13:44,124 --> 01:13:48,670
他的电脑发现"岩浆移位"
He's had intermittent contact with a magma displacement. He's got this...

790
01:13:48,837 --> 01:13:52,924
岩浆移位? 那不是地震学的问题吗?
Magma displacement? Is that like a seismic anomaly?

791
01:13:53,091 --> 01:13:55,906
应该是的  怎么了
I suppose so. Why?

792
01:13:55,906 --> 01:13:58,722
-可否让我登上达拉斯号?  -去干什么?
-Is there a way you could get me on board the Dallas?  -What for?

793
01:13:58,889 --> 01:14:01,787
曼库索找到红十月号
Help Captain Mancuso found the Red October.

794
01:14:01,787 --> 01:14:04,686
他什么都没找到  他只是在等待
He hasn't found anything, Jack. He's just waiting.

795
01:14:04,853 --> 01:14:07,188
长官
Excuse me, sir.

796
01:14:07,188 --> 01:14:09,524
无声推进系统经常被误认为...
But this silent propulsion system could easily be mistaken for something...

797
01:14:09,691 --> 01:14:13,153
只能坐直升机去达拉斯号
Jack, the only way to get you to the Dallas out there is by chopper.

798
01:14:13,320 --> 01:14:18,241
直升机可没有这么多燃料
is to use a chopper turned into a flying gas can.

799
01:14:18,408 --> 01:14:23,455
救援扬基一号的部队准备好了
Excuse me, Admiral. Yankee One is on final. Rescue personnel are in place.

800
01:14:23,622 --> 01:14:26,333
提升左翼
Pick up your left wing.

801
01:14:26,500 --> 01:14:28,877
禁止着陆!
Power! Wave off!

802
01:14:29,044 --> 01:14:32,047
座舱弹射!
Eject!

803
01:14:45,352 --> 01:14:51,066
这件事  会一发不可收拾
This business will get out of control and we'll be lucky to live through it.

804
01:15:03,787 --> 01:15:06,041
燃料倒是够
The bird's loaded down with enough fuel to get you there,

805
01:15:06,047 --> 01:15:08,041
不过达拉斯号可能会离开原地点
but Dallas may not be there.

806
01:15:08,208 --> 01:15:10,961
我们正在尝试联系它
We're trying to get message to her.

807
01:15:10,961 --> 01:15:13,714
如果它下潜了  如果你要跳伞
If she's gone deep, it's dodgey. If you have to ditch...

808
01:15:21,722 --> 01:15:25,434
如果要跳伞  记得拿求生装备
If you have to ditch, don't think about anything but the survival gear.

809
01:15:25,601 --> 01:15:31,522
-这种水温  你只能坚持四分钟
-At this water temperature, you'll have about four minutes.

810
01:15:32,192 --> 01:15:37,863
-我会记住的  下次记在备忘录上算了
-I'll try to remember that. Next time, Jack, write a goddamn memo.

811
01:16:10,938 --> 01:16:14,650
-船长睡了?  -是的
-Is the captain sacked out?  -Yeah.

812
01:16:15,817 --> 01:16:19,863
-他怎么样  -他不愿离开
-What about him?  -He won't leave.

813
01:16:28,830 --> 01:16:33,085
我见过美人鱼
You know, I've seen a mermaid once.

814
01:16:33,251 --> 01:16:37,172
还见过鲨鱼吃八爪鱼
I've even seen a shark eat an octopus.

815
01:16:37,339 --> 01:16:41,593
但没见过鬼魅一般的苏联潜艇
But I've never seen a phantom Russian submarine.

816
01:17:20,215 --> 01:17:23,697
我们会探测情况
We're emerging from the route, Captain.

817
01:17:23,697 --> 01:17:25,180
缓冲板会按正常程序进行清理
I've ordered a routine clearing of the baffles.

818
01:17:25,197 --> 01:17:27,180
在数分钟后转向
We'll be making the first turn in a few minutes.

819
01:17:27,347 --> 01:17:33,437
履带推进系统恢复正常工作
The caterpillar is operational and appears to be running normally.

820
01:17:33,604 --> 01:17:39,484
内奸的事令船员人心惶惶
The crew know about the saboteur and they are afraid.

821
01:17:41,403 --> 01:17:45,365
可以在适当时机利用这心态
Well, that could be useful when the time comes.

822
01:17:47,701 --> 01:17:53,123
十六小时后  会到达拉布拉多海岸
You know, we could make the Labrador Coast in 16 hours.

823
01:17:53,290 --> 01:17:56,918
那里太冷  船员会冻死
Half of them would freeze before they were rescued.

824
01:17:57,085 --> 01:18:01,131
四十八小时后  到马萨诸塞或缅因州
It's Massachusetts or Maine in 48 hours.

825
01:18:01,298 --> 01:18:04,509
两天
Two days.

826
01:18:11,058 --> 01:18:16,104
他们会不会让我住在蒙大拿州?
Do you think they will let me live in Montana?

827
01:18:21,526 --> 01:18:26,615
你想住哪里都可以
I would think they'll let you live wherever you want.

828
01:18:26,782 --> 01:18:32,204
好  我会住在蒙大拿州
Good, then I will live in Montana.

829
01:18:32,371 --> 01:18:37,167
娶一个肥胖的美国妻子  养兔子
I will marry a round American woman and raise rabbits.

830
01:18:37,334 --> 01:18:40,837
她会为我做饭
And she will cook them for me.

831
01:18:41,004 --> 01:18:44,675
我会买一辆小货车
And I will have a pickup truck.

832
01:18:44,841 --> 01:18:51,139
可能还会买一辆旅行车
Or possibly even a recreational vehicle...

833
01:18:51,306 --> 01:18:55,310
开着旅行车穿州过省
and drive from state to state.

834
01:18:55,477 --> 01:18:59,606
-可以这样做?  -是的
-Do they let you do that?  -Yes.

835
01:18:59,773 --> 01:19:04,444
-不必申请?  -无须申请  穿州过省
-No papers?  -No papers. State to state.

836
01:19:04,611 --> 01:19:07,823
好  开始转向
All right. Commence your turn.

837
01:19:10,909 --> 01:19:17,082
冬天住在亚利桑那州
Well then... in winter, I will live in Arizona.

838
01:19:17,249 --> 01:19:22,838
-我需要两个妻子  -至少两个
-Actually, I think I will need two wives.  -Oh, at least.

839
01:19:32,514 --> 01:19:39,271
-目标可能想转向  -是的  方位变了
-Possible aspect change on target.  -Sonar, Concur, change in bearing rate.

840
01:19:42,733 --> 01:19:46,987
-指挥室  疯狂伊凡!  -停车  保持安静
-Conn! Sonar! Crazy Ivan!  -All stop. Quick quiet!

841
01:19:54,661 --> 01:19:57,893
发生了什么  钟斯?
What's going on, Jonesy?

842
01:19:57,893 --> 01:20:01,126
苏联潜艇会突然急转  以探查自己是否被跟踪
Russian captains sometimes turn suddenly to see if anyone's behind them.

843
01:20:01,293 --> 01:20:04,630
我们称之为"疯狂伊凡"
We call it Crazy Ivan.

844
01:20:04,796 --> 01:20:07,465
我们要关掉所有机器
The only thing you can do is go dead, shut everything down...

845
01:20:07,465 --> 01:20:10,135
销声匿迹
and make like a hole in the water.

846
01:20:10,302 --> 01:20:16,934
-还有什么问题?  -大船不能一下子停下来
-So what's the catch? -Catch is a boat this big doesn't exactly stop on a dime.

847
01:20:17,100 --> 01:20:22,564
如果我们太近  会被卷进它的船尾
If we're too close, we'll drift right into the back of him.

848
01:20:24,733 --> 01:20:28,195
你呢  有什么心愿?
What about you? What do you look forward to?

849
01:20:37,454 --> 01:20:42,960
我再没有这种心情
I have no such appetites.

850
01:20:43,126 --> 01:20:46,964
看看他们能否能听见我们
Let's see if he can hear us.

851
01:20:51,677 --> 01:20:54,179
一定还有事情想做
There must be something.

852
01:21:02,104 --> 01:21:05,274
你想做什么?
What is it?

853
01:21:07,401 --> 01:21:12,030
我怀念小时候
I miss the peace of fishing.

854
01:21:12,197 --> 01:21:15,909
宁静地钓鱼的日子
Like when I was a boy.

855
01:21:17,452 --> 01:21:24,084
四十年来  我一直航海  海上的战争
40 years I've been sailing at sea. A war at sea.

856
01:21:26,086 --> 01:21:33,093
一场没有战役的战争  没有纪念碑
A war with no battles. No monuments.

857
01:21:33,260 --> 01:21:36,680
只有死伤者
Only casualties.

858
01:21:40,058 --> 01:21:44,021
妻子在结婚当日  变成寡妇
I widowed her the day I married her.

859
01:21:47,149 --> 01:21:50,694
她去世的时候  我还在船上
My wife died while I was at sea.

860
01:22:09,338 --> 01:22:12,424
找人看守轮机舱
Post guards in the engineering spaces.

861
01:22:12,591 --> 01:22:17,429
弄坏履带的人  会做出更严重的破坏
If he can get to the caterpillar, he can get to somewhere more vital.

862
01:22:20,349 --> 01:22:23,164
钟斯  他在那里?
Where is he, Jonesy?

863
01:22:23,164 --> 01:22:25,979
目标在我们右舷
Conn, Sonar. Target is now coming out of our starboard baffles.

864
01:22:26,146 --> 01:22:30,484
他想回到原来的路线
My read is that he's returning to base course.

865
01:22:30,651 --> 01:22:36,365
-他回到航线210  -他环绕我们
-Concur, he's returning to course 210.  -He went right around us.

866
01:22:36,531 --> 01:22:41,578
等三十秒  然后取消静航
Give him another 30 seconds. Then secure from silent running.

867
01:22:41,745 --> 01:22:46,375
我们收到讯息
Captain, here's what we got on the ELF.

868
01:22:48,335 --> 01:22:50,921
-谢谢  -不用谢  长官
-Thanks.  -Aye, sir.

869
01:22:58,095 --> 01:23:01,932
是什么?
What is it?

870
01:23:02,099 --> 01:23:05,185
你绝对不相信
You're not going to believe this.

871
01:23:17,489 --> 01:23:19,658
我们要及早返航
Commander, we're approaching no return.

872
01:23:19,658 --> 01:23:21,827
达拉斯号没收到信息
Dallas apparently hasn't gotten the message.

873
01:23:21,994 --> 01:23:24,225
-我们要返航  -再等一会儿
-We have to turn back.  -Give it a couple more minutes.

874
01:23:24,225 --> 01:23:26,456
不行  燃料快不够了
Negative. Fuel status says we turn around now.

875
01:23:26,623 --> 01:23:30,752
等等  你们没有后备燃料吗?
Wait a minute. Fuel status? You got a reserve, don't you?

876
01:23:30,919 --> 01:23:32,983
我有十分钟后备燃料
Yes, sir. I've got a ten minute reserve.

877
01:23:32,983 --> 01:23:35,048
但只有作战时才可动用
But I'm not allowed to invade that except during war.

878
01:23:35,215 --> 01:23:39,970
如果你不让我上潜艇  战争会爆发
Mr. If you don't get me on that goddamn submarine, you might have it.

879
01:23:40,137 --> 01:23:44,308
如果有燃料  我们再等十分钟吧
You got 10 minutes worth of fuel. we stay here ten more minutes.

880
01:23:47,811 --> 01:23:53,275
东边两英里处发现潜艇
Yo! Mount up! Yo, I got a submarine at around 3:00. About two miles.

881
01:23:55,611 --> 01:23:57,946
好  给他戴上工具
Okay, Tony, hook him up.

882
01:23:57,946 --> 01:24:00,282
好的  我们把你放到潜艇下面去
OK, Commander. I'll be lowering you down to the submarine now.

883
01:24:00,449 --> 01:24:05,245
希望这东西能把烟当作燃料
Give me eight minutes. Let's hope this thing runs on fumes.

884
01:24:05,412 --> 01:24:11,293
浮上海面  这家伙要吃苦了
Very well. Surface the ship. Whoever this guy is, he's in for one hell of a ride.

885
01:24:11,460 --> 01:24:14,963
好了  坐下来
Okay, Commander, go ahead and sit down.

886
01:24:15,130 --> 01:24:20,302
-有经验吗?  -试过一次  当时风平浪静
-Did you ever do this before?  -Once, on a calm day... off Hawaii.

887
01:24:20,469 --> 01:24:24,056
直升机无法稳定地飞行
The pilot will have a difficult time keeping steady.

888
01:24:24,222 --> 01:24:27,392
拿着这棒  以防电击
Don't take chances getting grounded. Keep that rod in front of you.

889
01:24:27,559 --> 01:24:32,105
旋翼的静电  能点亮芝加哥城
In air like this, the rotors will be putting out enough static to light up Chicago.

890
01:24:32,272 --> 01:24:36,735
我预备了潜水员  他可能会坠海
A diver's in the escape trunk in case this guy goes in the drink.

891
01:24:36,902 --> 01:24:40,572
对  这疯子想玩命!
Someone must have a burr up his ass to go for a stunt like this.

892
01:25:05,013 --> 01:25:08,934
如果我要把你带上来  我会摇绳子和竖起大拇指
Commander, if I got to bring you back up, I'm going to shake the wire.

893
01:25:09,101 --> 01:25:13,981
两手交叉  记住了吗?
I'll give you a thumbs up, like this. Remember to cross your arms.

894
01:25:14,147 --> 01:25:17,317
好的  出发吧
Okay, out you go. Passenger's out the door.

895
01:25:24,491 --> 01:25:28,161
乘客出来了  在半空中往前荡
He's halfway down. You're drifting forward.

896
01:25:32,457 --> 01:25:35,794
好的  勾着他的绳
All right. Get the hook on his cable.

897
01:25:35,961 --> 01:25:40,007
注意  别碰他  他来了
Watch it! Don't touch him. Okay, here he comes.

898
01:25:46,888 --> 01:25:51,226
风太大了  我看不见他
It'd be easier without that crosswind. I can't see him.

899
01:25:53,687 --> 01:25:56,565
别碰他
Don't touch him!

900
01:26:01,153 --> 01:26:05,741
-行不通  -拉他回来吧
-This is never going to work.  -OK. Reel him back in.

901
01:26:12,706 --> 01:26:15,584
托尼  他怎么了...
Tony, what's the hell going on back...

902
01:26:18,462 --> 01:26:21,381
达拉斯号  有没有准备潜水员?
Dallas, have you got a swimmer?

903
01:26:21,548 --> 01:26:26,178
有人在左舷坠海  派出潜水员
Man overboard, port side. Send out the diver.

904
01:26:26,345 --> 01:26:30,349
好的  达拉斯号  我们要走了
Very well. Dallas, we are history.

905
01:26:37,898 --> 01:26:42,152
救下面那位博士  我去逃生舱
Get the doc down here. I'll be in the escape trunk.

906
01:26:45,280 --> 01:26:49,242
拿梯子来  打开舱盖
Down ladder. Make a hole.

907
01:27:04,841 --> 01:27:09,554
你好  舰长  我很高兴能上舰
How do you do, Captain? It's a pleasure to be aboard.

908
01:27:11,848 --> 01:27:15,519
我要跟总统说话
I have to talk to the President.

909
01:27:15,686 --> 01:27:19,147
好的  请问为何事?
Of course. May I enquire as to the subject?

910
01:27:20,941 --> 01:27:24,256
看来我们先前的报告不太准确
It seems that the initial reports that...

911
01:27:24,256 --> 01:27:27,572
我们的潜艇没有失踪
one of our submarines was missing were not completely accurate.

912
01:27:29,658 --> 01:27:34,913
该艘潜艇由马尔科·雷米斯指挥
The submarine in question is commanded by Captain Marko Ramius.

913
01:27:35,080 --> 01:27:40,585
他陷入精神崩溃的状态
Apparently, he has suffered a kind of mental nervous breakdown.

914
01:27:42,087 --> 01:27:48,343
在出发前  他寄信给巴度宁上将
Just before he sailed, he posted a letter to Admiral Padorin...

915
01:27:48,510 --> 01:27:51,388
他宣称  想向美国...
in which he announced his intention to...

916
01:27:53,599 --> 01:27:56,643
发射导弹
to fire his missiles on the United States.

917
01:27:58,312 --> 01:28:01,064
上次为什么不告诉我?
Why didn't you tell me this the last time we met?

918
01:28:01,231 --> 01:28:03,566
莫斯科不会
In my position I'm sometimes compromised...

919
01:28:03,566 --> 01:28:05,902
告诉我所有事情
by the fact Moscow doesn't always tell me everything.

920
01:28:06,069 --> 01:28:10,866
你们的潜艇舰长疯了? 你要我们怎么做?
So one of your submarine captains has gone insane? What do you want from us?

921
01:28:11,033 --> 01:28:14,369
需要你们帮个忙
You offered your assistance.

922
01:28:14,369 --> 01:28:17,706
本来是个营救行动  现在你让我们帮你除掉他
That was a rescue mission. Now you want us to help you hunt him down and kill him.

923
01:28:19,124 --> 01:28:24,171
我奉命来请贵国总统帮忙
I have been instructed to ask your president for precisely that.

924
01:28:24,338 --> 01:28:29,718
我们已经找到他  但我们要为你停下来
Find him? We already found him. We had to break off to pick you up.

925
01:28:29,885 --> 01:28:34,139
-喝杯咖啡  还是抽支烟?  -我不抽烟
-Coffee. A cigarette?  -I don't smoke.

926
01:28:34,306 --> 01:28:39,102
假设我们找到他  然后怎么办?
Assuming we can find him, just what exactly am I supposed to do about it?

927
01:28:39,269 --> 01:28:43,523
舰长  通讯室报告  收到紧急讯号
Captain, radio. We're receiving flash traffic on the emergency circuit.

928
01:28:43,690 --> 01:28:45,859
好的  翻译它
Very well. Bring it down.

929
01:28:47,444 --> 01:28:50,155
瑞恩先生
Well, Mr. Ryan?

930
01:28:51,990 --> 01:28:56,411
-大副  让我们单独谈谈  -雷纳德  过来
-Chief, excuse us for a second.  -Leonard, come on out of there.

931
01:29:02,793 --> 01:29:05,796
我们在追踪红十月号
The sub we're after is called the Red October.

932
01:29:05,796 --> 01:29:08,799
舰长是马尔科·雷米斯
She's under the command of a man named Ramius.

933
01:29:08,966 --> 01:29:11,739
他和艇上部分军官
Now, there's the possibility that he and a good portion...

934
01:29:11,739 --> 01:29:14,513
可能想叛变
of his crew are attempting to defect.

935
01:29:16,932 --> 01:29:19,851
叛变?
Defect?

936
01:29:20,018 --> 01:29:22,145
对不起
Excuse me.

937
01:29:38,620 --> 01:29:41,247
-那潜艇叫红十月号?  -对
-You say the boat's called the Red October?  -That's right.

938
01:29:41,247 --> 01:29:43,875
-舰长是雷米斯?  -对
-Skipper's Ramius?  -Right.

939
01:29:44,042 --> 01:29:49,214
看来形势转变了  瑞恩
It seems that circumstances have changed somewhat, Mr. Ryan.

940
01:29:56,179 --> 01:30:00,309
-给他干衣服  我在指挥台等他  -遵命  舰长
-Get this man some dry clothes. I'll be in the conn.  -Aye, sir.

941
01:30:00,475 --> 01:30:02,852
"苏军潜艇红十月号舰长
"National Command Authority informed Soviet typhoon class submarine...

942
01:30:02,852 --> 01:30:05,230
马尔科·雷米斯
Red October Marko Ramius...

943
01:30:05,397 --> 01:30:10,152
可能叛变  准备擅自发射导弹"
is potential renegade and threatens independent missile launch.

944
01:30:10,319 --> 01:30:13,509
"你有权采取任何行动
"You are authorized to use any necessary force...

945
01:30:13,509 --> 01:30:16,700
防止它接近美国海岸"
to prevent said submarine from approaching the coast of the United States."

946
01:30:31,048 --> 01:30:35,969
左转10度  航向265
Left 10 degrees rudder steady on course 265.

947
01:30:39,806 --> 01:30:42,684
舱内亮红色灯
Chief of the Watch, rig for red.

948
01:30:52,986 --> 01:30:55,468
-什么事?  -已部署好战斗岗位
-What's going on?  -Battle stations are manned and ready, Captain.

949
01:30:55,468 --> 01:30:57,950
很好
Very well.

950
01:30:58,116 --> 01:31:01,223
舰长  我要跟你谈谈
Captain, I have to talk to you.

951
01:31:01,223 --> 01:31:04,331
现在不行  潜至一千二百英尺  俯倾20度
Not now. Tommy, make your depth 1,200 feet, 20 degrees down angle.

952
01:31:04,498 --> 01:31:09,836
潜水官  潜至一千二百英尺  俯倾20度
Diving officer, make your depth 1,200 feet, 20 degrees down.

953
01:31:10,003 --> 01:31:15,884
全速下潜
Full dive on fair water planes. Full dive on stern planes.

954
01:31:18,762 --> 01:31:22,599
450英尺  潜至1200英尺
Passing 450 feet, going to 1,200.

955
01:31:22,766 --> 01:31:25,519
500英尺
500.

956
01:31:26,895 --> 01:31:29,690
600英尺
600.

957
01:31:29,856 --> 01:31:33,151
700英尺
700.

958
01:31:36,947 --> 01:31:40,575
-一切顺利?  -是的  舰长
-Did you get a good fix?  -Yes, Captain.

959
01:31:47,165 --> 01:31:52,129
-钟斯  发现他了吗?  -很微弱  舰长  正在监听
-Sonar, conn, have you got him yet, Jonesy?  -Very faint, sir. Hold on.

960
01:31:53,672 --> 01:31:58,176
250方位  发现台风七号  在我们预想的位置
Yes, sir. Contact typhoon seven on bearing 250. Right where he's supposed to be.

961
01:31:58,343 --> 01:32:02,889
-他有否发觉我们?  -没有
-Any sign he's alerted to our presence?  -No. Operating as before.

962
01:32:03,056 --> 01:32:08,145
左转到265  溜到他们背后
Come left to 265. Bring us up behind him quietly, Tommy.

963
01:32:08,312 --> 01:32:10,897
再下潜五百英尺
Make your depth 500 feet.

964
01:32:20,073 --> 01:32:23,493
舰长  让我说两分钟
Please listen to me. Two minutes, that's all.

965
01:32:25,495 --> 01:32:29,750
-导航  何时能进入它的航道?  -四分钟后
-Plot, time to intercept his track.  -Four minutes, Captain.

966
01:32:29,916 --> 01:32:33,253
好吧  给你两分钟  瑞恩
Very well, Mr. Ryan. Two minutes.

967
01:32:39,843 --> 01:32:43,764
那些指示很合理  但实情是...
I understand that message, it makes perfect sense. But the situation is...

968
01:32:43,931 --> 01:32:46,266
雷米斯想叛变
Ramius intends to defect.

969
01:32:46,266 --> 01:32:48,602
所以苏军一直想击沉他
The Russians know this, which is why they've tried to sink him...

970
01:32:48,769 --> 01:32:51,021
-但他们无能为力  -发炮程式准备好了
-but they haven't been able to. So... -I have a firing solution.

971
01:32:51,021 --> 01:32:53,273
很好
Very well.

972
01:32:53,440 --> 01:32:55,546
舰长  听我说
Captain, you have to listen to me.

973
01:32:55,546 --> 01:32:57,653
苏军想要不惜一切代价阻止雷米斯叛变
The Russians will stop at nothing to prevent Ramius from defecting.

974
01:32:57,819 --> 01:33:00,676
所以他们骗我们说他疯了
They've invented this story that he's crazy...

975
01:33:00,676 --> 01:33:03,533
想让我们击沉他
because they need us to sink him before he can contact us.

976
01:33:05,869 --> 01:33:11,416
启动保安系统  我不想鱼雷反过来对付我们
Weapons control, I want full safeties. I don't want this fish coming back.

977
01:33:11,583 --> 01:33:14,836
舰长  我认识这个人
Captain, I know this man.

978
01:33:15,879 --> 01:33:18,840
他有没有做"疯狂伊凡"?
Has he made any Crazy Ivans?

979
01:33:18,840 --> 01:33:21,802
-那有什么关系  -下一次是右转
-What difference does that make?  -His next one will be to starboard.

980
01:33:21,969 --> 01:33:26,932
因为过了三十分  他总会右转
Because he goes to starboard in the bottom half of the hour.

981
01:33:29,726 --> 01:33:32,604
调整1号2号鱼雷管  准备发炮
Flood tubes one and two. Warm up the weapons.

982
01:33:32,771 --> 01:33:35,317
舰长  设法跟他联络吧
Captain, find a way to establish contact without violating orders.

983
01:33:35,321 --> 01:33:37,317
他想叛变!
He wants to defect!

984
01:33:37,484 --> 01:33:42,489
叫沃森拿枪到指挥室来
Mr. Thompson, Call Chief Watson to the conn with his sidearm.

985
01:33:46,410 --> 01:33:50,914
声纳讯号转变  目标方位变化
Conn, Sonar. Signal to noise ratio's dropping. Possible aspect change in target.

986
01:33:51,081 --> 01:33:54,418
目标可能在移动
Possible target zig based on bearing rate.

987
01:33:55,585 --> 01:33:58,171
疯狂伊凡
Conn, Sonar. Crazy Ivan!

988
01:34:00,882 --> 01:34:05,470
舰长  他转过来了
Captain, he's turning.

989
01:34:08,849 --> 01:34:12,686
-他向哪边转?  -右转
-Which way is he turning, Jonesy?  -To the starboard, sir!

990
01:34:12,853 --> 01:34:16,565
给他个机会
Give the man a chance.

991
01:34:18,483 --> 01:34:21,403
-全速后退  -舰长  再说一遍
-All back full.  -Captain, say again.

992
01:34:21,570 --> 01:34:24,865
-全速后退!  -是  长官
-I said all back full!  -Back full. Aye, sir.

993
01:34:29,661 --> 01:34:35,626
-水里形成空洞  他会听见我们  -停车
-Captain, we're cavitating! He can hear us.  -Conn, aye. All stop.

994
01:34:36,335 --> 01:34:38,879
我们暴露了行踪
All right. We just unzipped our fly.

995
01:34:39,046 --> 01:34:44,217
开启外门  准备开火
Mr. Thompson, open the outer doors. Firing point procedures.

996
01:34:44,384 --> 01:34:48,513
只要他有任何异动  我会立刻发炮
Now, if that bastard so much as twitches, I'm going to blow him right to Mars.

997
01:34:48,680 --> 01:34:51,433
停车  回舵到0度
All stop rudder amid ship.

998
01:34:51,600 --> 01:34:54,978
能否辨认对方?
Can you identify the contact?

999
01:34:55,145 --> 01:34:57,772
美国洛杉矶级潜艇  方位: 015  距离: 300米
American Los Angeles-class attack submarine. Bearing: 015. Range: 300 metres.

1000
01:34:57,772 --> 01:35:00,400
舰长  瞬时金属声
Captain, sharp metallic transients.

1001
01:35:00,567 --> 01:35:03,278
他可能想打开鱼雷盖
He may be trying to open his torpedo tube doors.

1002
01:35:03,445 --> 01:35:06,657
外门开启了  准备开火
Outer doors are open on tubes one and two. We're ready to shoot.

1003
01:35:06,823 --> 01:35:11,328
好  我的命令很明确
Very well. My orders are specific, Mr. Ryan.

1004
01:35:11,495 --> 01:35:14,581
他开了外门  准备开火
Captain, he has opened his outer doors. He's preparing to fire.

1005
01:35:14,748 --> 01:35:19,586
调整3号4号鱼雷管  准备开火
Flood tubes three and four and plot a solution.

1006
01:35:21,880 --> 01:35:24,549
要不要打开鱼雷盖?
Shall I open the torpedo tube doors, sir?

1007
01:35:27,511 --> 01:35:32,849
-舰长  要开启外门吗?  -不
-Captain, shall I open outer doors?  -No.

1008
01:35:33,016 --> 01:35:36,812
用电脑记下发炮程序
Lock the firing solution into the computer.

1009
01:35:36,979 --> 01:35:40,023
千万不要开门
Do not open the doors.

1010
01:35:46,321 --> 01:35:52,286
是  舰长  向电脑输入发炮程序
Aye, Captain. Lock solution into computer.

1011
01:35:52,452 --> 01:35:57,499
-目标准备了鱼雷管  -他有没有开外门?
-Conn, Sonar. Target has flooded his tubes.  -Has he opened his outer doors?

1012
01:35:57,666 --> 01:36:01,878
没有  他按兵不动  等等
Negative, Captain. He's just sitting there. Hold on.

1013
01:36:02,587 --> 01:36:07,593
-目标在往上浮升  -那是什么意思?
-Target is coming shallow.  -What does that mean?

1014
01:36:09,553 --> 01:36:12,723
这位苏联人很聪明
It means he's a very cool customer, your Russian.

1015
01:36:12,889 --> 01:36:14,738
他知道我们已经准备好发炮
He knows we're here and ready to shoot.

1016
01:36:14,738 --> 01:36:16,587
他不想煽动我们发炮
He's not provoking us.

1017
01:36:16,587 --> 01:36:18,437
他上浮至潜望镜深度观察情况
He's heading to periscope depth to see what's on the surface.

1018
01:36:18,604 --> 01:36:22,774
-他在什么方位?  -270  向着西面
-What's his course now?  -His course is 270. Due west.

1019
01:36:22,941 --> 01:36:26,278
-我们靠近他  -遵命
-Bring us alongside him.  -Aye, Captain.

1020
01:36:26,445 --> 01:36:29,489
声纳有其他发现吗
Sonar, Conn. Report all contacts.

1021
01:36:29,656 --> 01:36:34,036
只有台风七号  方位195
Conn, Sonar. My only contact is Typhoon 7, bearing 195.

1022
01:36:34,202 --> 01:36:39,166
-很好  火控室  与目标的距离?  -距离300码
-Very well. Fire control, range to target?  -Range is 300 yards.

1023
01:36:40,667 --> 01:36:45,047
上升至六十五英尺
Make your depth 65 feet.

1024
01:36:46,256 --> 01:36:50,510
他想浮上去看个清楚  我们奉陪
He wants to go up and take a peek. We'll play along.

1025
01:37:10,405 --> 01:37:12,699
-武器情况如何?  -准备好了
-Weapons status?  -Weapons are on.

1026
01:37:12,866 --> 01:37:17,537
3号和4号鱼雷准备好了  但外门未开启
Tubes three and four are flooded, but outer doors are closed.

1027
01:37:20,037 --> 01:37:21,937
记录此位置
Mark this bearing.

1028
01:37:29,883 --> 01:37:36,139
你想跟他谈话吗? 他在这儿  你想说什么?
You wanted to talk to him, Mr. Ryan? There he is. What do you want to say?

1029
01:37:36,306 --> 01:37:40,519
-是他在看潜望镜吗?  -可能是吧
-Will he be the only one looking through the periscope?  -Probably.

1030
01:37:40,686 --> 01:37:44,022
我要冒险一试
We'll have to chance that.

1031
01:37:44,189 --> 01:37:48,360
"听说阁下想发射导弹"
"US told you intend missile launch."

1032
01:37:48,527 --> 01:37:53,949
"别接近美国海岸线  否则我们会进攻"
"Do not approach US coast or you will be attacked."

1033
01:37:54,116 --> 01:37:59,246
"如果另有意图  可否一起商议"
"If intention is other, will you discuss option?"

1034
01:38:00,163 --> 01:38:03,417
他可否以一下声响示意?
Can he acknowledge with a single ping?

1035
01:38:03,583 --> 01:38:07,629
可以  但他会答复吗?
Yeah, he can. The question is, will he?

1036
01:38:14,219 --> 01:38:19,850
表明目标距离  响一声
Verify our range to target. One ping only.

1037
01:38:21,268 --> 01:38:23,854
是  舰长
Aye, Captain.

1038
01:38:29,443 --> 01:38:32,904
是真的  现在怎样?
I'll be damned. Now what?

1039
01:38:35,157 --> 01:38:39,202
好  "如要叛变"
All right. "If defection..."

1040
01:38:45,959 --> 01:38:50,631
我要一张航海图
Chart. I need a chart.

1041
01:38:52,716 --> 01:38:57,512
我们在哪里? 一个水深的地方...
OK. Where the hell are we? Someplace deep. Someplace deep...

1042
01:38:58,212 --> 01:38:59,632
劳伦深渊

1043
01:38:59,932 --> 01:39:03,560
好  发出这讯息
Okay, send him this.

1044
01:39:06,855 --> 01:39:11,151
-你疯了吗?  -只管照着发吧
-Are you out of your mind?  -Just send it.

1045
01:39:14,404 --> 01:39:19,618
告诉我  你怎知道他会右转
Tell me one thing. How did you know he was going to go to starboard?

1046
01:39:19,785 --> 01:39:25,248
我不知道  我想碰碰运气来打断你  对不起
I didn't. I had a 50-50 chance and I needed a break. Sorry.

1047
01:39:27,084 --> 01:39:30,587
不要紧  很久没使用摩斯密码...
That's all right, Mr. Ryan. My Morse is so rusty...

1048
01:39:30,754 --> 01:39:35,217
我可能发出了美女三围数字
I may be sending him dimensions on playmate of the month.

1049
01:39:53,902 --> 01:39:57,197
再次表明目标距离
Reverify our range to target.

1050
01:39:57,364 --> 01:40:01,868
-只响一声  -舰长  我刚...
-One ping only.  -Captain, I just...

1051
01:40:02,035 --> 01:40:06,373
请再发出一声声响  瓦西里  只响一声
Give me a ping, Vassily. One ping only, please.

1052
01:40:09,334 --> 01:40:11,753
是  舰长
Aye, Captain.

1053
01:40:15,591 --> 01:40:18,844
这是什么意思?
What the hell is this about?

1054
01:40:19,011 --> 01:40:24,766
苏联人希望我们击沉它  我们可能真的要这么做了
The Russians want us to sink her. We might have to do that.

1055
01:40:32,482 --> 01:40:36,486
我们要给美国人一点回旋余地
We must give this American a wide berth.

1056
01:40:37,529 --> 01:40:41,199
转向南边
And let us turn south.

1057
01:40:49,499 --> 01:40:55,964
卡马洛夫先生  计划航线  往南走
Mr. Kamarov, plot a new course due south.

1058
01:40:58,133 --> 01:41:01,053
新航向: 180
New course: 180.

1059
01:41:23,853 --> 01:41:29,053
大浅滩  劳伦深渊以北  二十小时后

1060
01:41:34,836 --> 01:41:38,173
-关闭反应堆  -遵命  长官
-Shut down the reactor.  -Aye, sir.

1061
01:41:38,340 --> 01:41:43,303
-封闭通风系统  -通风系统失控
-Seal the ventilation system.  -The ventilation controls have failed.

1062
01:41:43,470 --> 01:41:47,766
所有人离开船舱
Everybody out! Clear the compartment.

1063
01:41:58,193 --> 01:42:02,656
-关掉通风系统  -控制器没反应
-Ventilation system, shut it down now.  -They don't respond.

1064
01:42:02,823 --> 01:42:06,535
手动关闭它  快!
Bypass it. Seal it manually. Move!

1065
01:42:07,869 --> 01:42:10,664
再说一遍
Melekhin, say again.

1066
01:42:17,588 --> 01:42:20,591
冷却管破裂
Suffered a leak in the primary coolant tube...

1067
01:42:20,591 --> 01:42:23,594
反应堆停止  通风电路关闭
so shut down the reactor, but the ventilation circuits have been disabled.

1068
01:42:23,760 --> 01:42:26,429
冷却液严重污染
The coolant appears highly contaminated.

1069
01:42:26,429 --> 01:42:29,099
自从履带损坏  我早知道会这样
I knew there was damage when the caterpillar went down.

1070
01:42:29,266 --> 01:42:31,045
所有部门都发出辐射警告
Captain, radiation alarms are activated in all compartments.

1071
01:42:31,045 --> 01:42:34,605
轮机舱严重污染  辐射继续扩散
Engineering is heavily contaminated, and radiation's moving forward.

1072
01:42:34,771 --> 01:42:37,315
上浮至潜望镜深度  通入新鲜空气
Get us to periscope depth. We'll ventilate with outside air.

1073
01:42:37,315 --> 01:42:39,860
遵命  上浮至潜望镜深度
Aye, Captain. Periscope depth.

1074
01:42:40,027 --> 01:42:44,364
-准备换气  -换气是不够的  我们要疏散船员
Prepare to ventilate! Ventilating won't do anything. We've got to get them off.

1075
01:42:44,531 --> 01:42:48,452
-电池可维持多久?  -4个小时  最多6个小时
-What is the battery condition?  -Four hours. Six, if we're cautious.

1076
01:42:48,619 --> 01:42:51,288
启动电池系统
Engage battery system.

1077
01:42:51,288 --> 01:42:52,957
这是一级辐射泄漏
Captain, we've got a level one radiation leak.

1078
01:42:52,958 --> 01:42:53,957
全艇遭受污染
Every surface of this ship's contaminated.

1079
01:42:54,124 --> 01:42:57,586
我们必须疏散船员
We've got to get the men off.

1080
01:42:57,753 --> 01:43:00,839
舰长  有人蓄意破坏潜艇
Sir, we have been sabotaged.

1081
01:43:01,006 --> 01:43:04,468
-谁说有人蓄意毁坏?  舰长!
-Who said anything about sabotage?  -Captain!

1082
01:43:04,635 --> 01:43:07,971
舰长  医生可能说得对
Sir, I'm afraid the doctor's right.

1083
01:43:12,392 --> 01:43:17,981
好吧  浮上水面  将船员疏散到甲板上
Very well. Surface. We'll evacuate the men to the deck.

1084
01:43:18,148 --> 01:43:23,236
遵命  浮上水面  所有人员前往逃生舱准备逃生
Captain. Surface the ship. Prepare to muster all personnel to escape hatches.

1085
01:43:23,403 --> 01:43:27,160
甲板准备救生艇
Break out the rafts. Lash them to the deck.

1086
01:43:27,203 --> 01:43:30,160
等待舰队救援
We'll use them as shelters until the fleet arrives.

1087
01:44:12,327 --> 01:44:18,041
-医生  点算人数  不能留下船员  -遵命
-Make sure the count is accurate, Doctor. We must get the entire crew out.

1088
01:44:18,208 --> 01:44:25,132
-武器官报告  救生艇启用  正在疏散  -很好
-Master at Arms reports rafts secure and evacuation proceeding.  -Very good.

1089
01:44:30,679 --> 01:44:32,662
轮流值班
We'll rotate through the conn.

1090
01:44:32,669 --> 01:44:34,662
军官不要逗留在甲板上超过二十分钟
No officer will spend more than 20 minutes below deck.

1091
01:44:34,662 --> 01:44:38,645
同意  舰长
Completely, Captain.

1092
01:44:38,812 --> 01:44:44,901
发现船只  方位: 270  距离6英里并快速接近中
Surface contact: 270. Six miles and closing fast.

1093
01:44:45,068 --> 01:44:48,947
-是战舰!  -什么战舰?
-It's a warship!  -Here? Can you identify?

1094
01:44:49,114 --> 01:44:54,786
可能是美军佩里级驱逐舰  它在发讯号
It's a frigate, U.S, probably, Perry class. He's signaling.

1095
01:44:54,953 --> 01:45:00,709
红十月号  停止航行
Red October, Red October, halt and stay where you are.

1096
01:45:00,876 --> 01:45:04,379
别尝试下潜  否则我们会发炮
Do not attempt to submerge or you will be fired upon.

1097
01:45:07,132 --> 01:45:09,968
舰长  好像他们想登艇
Captain, I think he means to board us.

1098
01:45:16,183 --> 01:45:21,813
你跟船员离开  我和军官留下
You will go with the crew. The officers and I will submerge beneath you...

1099
01:45:21,980 --> 01:45:27,277
-我们会摧毁潜艇  -你会为此得到列宁勋章
-and scuttle the ship. -You will receive the Order of Lenin for this, Captain.

1100
01:45:37,245 --> 01:45:42,793
我们离船  舰长会跟潜艇一起沉没
Prepare to cast off. The captain is going to scuttle the ship.

1101
01:45:47,631 --> 01:45:52,052
-他下潜了  舰长  -发炮掠过艇首  右转到航向180
-He's going down, sir.  -Put a shot across his bow. Come right at 180.

1102
01:46:22,457 --> 01:46:25,210
海鹰一号  我是指挥部
Seahawk One, this is Bravo Command.

1103
01:46:43,770 --> 01:46:47,024
它准备好了
She's ready.

1104
01:46:47,190 --> 01:46:49,985
海鹰一号  听我的命令
Seahawk One, release on my command.

1105
01:46:50,152 --> 01:46:52,738
现在发射
Drop now...now...now.

1106
01:47:01,330 --> 01:47:05,876
距目标900码... 800码...
Range to target 900 yards... 800 yards...

1107
01:47:08,128 --> 01:47:13,508
700码... 600码...
700 yards... 600 yards...

1108
01:47:18,597 --> 01:47:24,061
500码... 400码...
500 yards... 400 yards...

1109
01:47:26,188 --> 01:47:28,690
300码
300 yards.

1110
01:47:31,151 --> 01:47:34,154
鱼雷被引爆了
The torpedo is detonated.

1111
01:47:34,321 --> 01:47:37,616
指挥员  听着
Now, understand, Commander...

1112
01:47:37,616 --> 01:47:40,911
那鱼雷没有自我毁灭  你听到它撞到船体
that torpedo did not self-destruct. You heard it hit the hull.

1113
01:47:41,078 --> 01:47:45,040
我没有来过这里
And I was never here.

1114
01:47:45,207 --> 01:47:50,379
-通知达拉斯号  -派出深潜救助艇
-Contact Dallas. Give them the go.  -Advise Dallas. Get the DSRV moving.

1115
01:47:59,054 --> 01:48:03,058
200万的东西仍然会在表演特技时出差错
Two million things can still go wrong with this stunt.

1116
01:48:03,225 --> 01:48:08,897
中情局的人真没头脑
Central Intelligence Agency... there's a contradiction in terms.

1117
01:48:09,940 --> 01:48:12,776
咖啡味道如何  瑞恩?
How's the coffee, Ryan?

1118
01:48:12,943 --> 01:48:18,615
达拉斯号  神秘号准备出发
Dallas, this is the Mystic. Request clearance to launch.

1119
01:48:19,908 --> 01:48:25,956
-舱盖盖好了  -一切正常  准备出发
-Hatch is secured.  -Life support, normal. Prelaunch checks complete.

1120
01:48:26,123 --> 01:48:31,503
-向外周注水  -外周注水  已平衡
-Flood the skirt.  -Skirt filled and equalized.

1121
01:48:31,670 --> 01:48:36,091
-可以启航  -好的  启航吧
-Ready to lift off.  -Okay, let's do it.

1122
01:48:38,719 --> 01:48:41,597
推往左舷
Thrusting to port.

1123
01:49:01,325 --> 01:49:07,414
-距离600码  接近中  -右转到075
-600 yards and closing.  -Steer right to course 075.

1124
01:49:12,377 --> 01:49:17,591
200码...  100码
200 yards... 100 yards.

1125
01:49:24,973 --> 01:49:27,559
开灯
Hit the lights.

1126
01:49:39,780 --> 01:49:43,200
这家伙真大
Jesus! That's a big sucker.

1127
01:49:59,383 --> 01:50:03,637
-位置正确  -可以打开舱盖
-Okay, we're in position.  -You can open the hatch.

1128
01:50:03,804 --> 01:50:10,310
等一会  钟斯...  瑞恩
Hold it a second. Jonesy...  Mr. Ryan.

1129
01:50:13,689 --> 01:50:18,986
-他想叛变  -他不会改变主意?
-He's defecting.  -And he can't change his mind?

1130
01:50:19,152 --> 01:50:24,199
-不会  -你敢以性命担保?
-He's not going to change his mind.  -Will you bet your life on that?

1131
01:50:44,261 --> 01:50:47,639
-舰长  请把锤子递给我  -好的
-Sir, could you hand me that hammer?  -Yeah.

1132
01:51:09,911 --> 01:51:14,166
美国人
Americans.

1133
01:52:53,557 --> 01:52:56,810
他脸色变青
He's turning green.

1134
01:53:14,911 --> 01:53:18,749
他像个牛仔
There's our buckaroo.

1135
01:53:19,917 --> 01:53:23,170
什么事这么好笑?
What's so funny?

1136
01:53:23,337 --> 01:53:27,341
舰长说你像牛仔
The captain thinks you're some sort of cowboy.

1137
01:53:27,507 --> 01:53:35,182
-你会俄语  -会一点
-You speak Russian.  -A little.

1138
01:53:35,349 --> 01:53:41,480
知己知彼  百战百胜
It's wise to study the ways of one's adversary.

1139
01:53:41,647 --> 01:53:43,732
说得对
It is.

1140
01:53:45,734 --> 01:53:50,697
你还记得吗  我们在列宁格勒领事馆见过面
I doubt you'd remember, but we met once at the consulate in Leningrad.

1141
01:53:50,864 --> 01:53:56,453
尊夫人的事  我很难过
Along with your wife. I'm very sorry.

1142
01:53:56,620 --> 01:54:01,375
为什么无故向我的船发炮?
What gives you the right to fire on my ship?

1143
01:54:01,541 --> 01:54:05,796
-你的讯息没有提及鱼雷  -瑞恩
-Your signal said nothing of a torpedo.  -Ryan.

1144
01:54:07,047 --> 01:54:09,862
我们要误导你的船员
It was necessary to maintain the illusion for your crew.

1145
01:54:09,862 --> 01:54:12,678
他们会获救吗?
My crew are being rescued, yes?

1146
01:54:12,844 --> 01:54:16,807
救援行动已开始
As we speak.

1147
01:54:18,934 --> 01:54:24,022
-是你发的讯号?  -是的
-You sent the signal?  -That's correct, sir.

1148
01:54:24,189 --> 01:54:30,112
你怎么知道我们的反应堆事故是假的?
Then how did you know our reactor accident was false?

1149
01:54:30,279 --> 01:54:33,407
我循常理推测的
That was a guess, but it seemed logical.

1150
01:54:40,080 --> 01:54:42,833
很好
Very well.

1151
01:54:45,502 --> 01:54:51,091
我把弹道导弹潜艇红十月号交出来
I present to you the ballistic missile submarine Red October.

1152
01:54:55,304 --> 01:55:01,852
我和军官们要求美国庇护
My officers and I request asylum in the United States of America.

1153
01:55:04,229 --> 01:55:09,693
幸会  我是达拉斯号的巴特·曼库索舰长
It's a pleasure, sir. Bart Mancuso, USS Dallas.

1154
01:55:11,903 --> 01:55:14,635
鱼雷  美国人又开火了
Torpedo. The Americans are shooting at us again.

1155
01:55:14,635 --> 01:55:18,067
声调太高了  这是苏联鱼雷
The pitch is too high. The torpedo's Russian.

1156
01:55:18,137 --> 01:55:21,388
还有鱼雷? 从哪里来
What do you mean another torpedo? Where the hell did it come from?

1157
01:55:21,455 --> 01:55:25,459
指挥室  声纳发现苏联雅夫级潜艇  呼号4-1
Conn, Sonar. New contact. Sierra 4-1. Alfa class Soviet submarine.

1158
01:55:28,795 --> 01:55:32,111
声纳  为何不引爆?
Sonar, why don't I have a detonation?

1159
01:55:32,111 --> 01:55:33,727
目标距离太近
The weapon enabled on the far side of the target.

1160
01:55:33,731 --> 01:55:35,427
鱼雷来不及引爆
It passed Red October before arming.

1161
01:55:35,594 --> 01:55:39,640
你计算错误  重新装填  以正确参数重新发射鱼雷
You had the wrong range. Fire again with the right setting and reload both tubes.

1162
01:55:39,806 --> 01:55:44,770
加强能源  叫深海救助艇离开
Get me power, and get that damn thing off my boat.

1163
01:55:44,937 --> 01:55:50,233
-有人向我们发射鱼雷  -混帐  走吧
-I think somebody shot a torpedo at us.  -No shit, Buckwheat. Get out of here.

1164
01:55:58,575 --> 01:56:02,996
舰长正在与他们交战
The captain is fighting them.

1165
01:56:05,874 --> 01:56:09,086
鲍罗丁  负责火控
Borodin, fire control.

1166
01:56:09,253 --> 01:56:14,091
-瑞恩  坐在这里  -我不是海军  我是中情局人员
-Ryan, sit here.  -I'm not a naval officer. I'm with the CIA.

1167
01:56:14,258 --> 01:56:18,470
-中情局?  -我只是为他们写书
-CIA?  -I'm not an agent. I just write books for the CIA.

1168
01:56:19,763 --> 01:56:22,849
不管这些  坐下来  照我的吩咐做
Whatever. Sit down. And do exactly what I tell you.

1169
01:56:23,016 --> 01:56:26,520
深潜救助艇已离开  苏联雅夫级潜艇在右舷八千码外
DSRV's away. There's a Russian alfa 8,000 yards to starboard.

1170
01:56:26,687 --> 01:56:32,901
-看来是科诺瓦洛夫号  -超速前进
-Captain, I think it's the Konovalov.  -Increase to flank.

1171
01:56:33,027 --> 01:56:38,031
-超速前进  怎么操作?  -这个旋钮  向右扭死
-Increase to flank. How?  -That knob. Turn right full.

1172
01:56:38,198 --> 01:56:42,244
-超速前进  右满舵  -他再次开火
-All ahead flank. Right full rudder.  -He's shooting again, sir.

1173
01:56:42,411 --> 01:56:45,581
部署战斗岗位
Put battle stations.

1174
01:56:50,586 --> 01:56:55,299
-鱼雷发射  方位315  -距离700码
-Torpedo in the water. Bearing 315.  -Make range 7,000 yards.

1175
01:56:55,465 --> 01:57:01,930
-右转到方位315  -朝着鱼雷冲过去
-Steer right 315.  -That's heading into the torpedo.

1176
01:57:02,097 --> 01:57:08,437
-距离六千码  -右转到方位315
-Estimate range 6,000 yards.  -Steer right 315.

1177
01:57:08,604 --> 01:57:12,858
不  瑞恩  千万别转方向  我们冲向鱼雷
No, that's wrong! Ryan, don't turn that goddamn wheel.

1178
01:57:13,025 --> 01:57:16,278
航向315
315.

1179
01:57:26,580 --> 01:57:30,709
-你想冲向鱼雷  -是的
-You're heading straight for that torpedo.  -Yes.

1180
01:57:30,876 --> 01:57:34,880
-什么?  -他冲向鱼雷
-Doing what?  -He's turned into the torpedo's path.

1181
01:57:35,047 --> 01:57:37,591
-什么?  -红十月号直接冲向鱼雷  长官
-What?  -Red October's turned directly into the torpedo's path, sir.

1182
01:57:37,591 --> 01:57:40,135
-他直接冲向鱼雷  -我的天
-Red October's turned directly into the torpedo's path, sir.  -Mother of God!

1183
01:57:40,302 --> 01:57:44,848
鱼雷在方位315  距离: 5000码
Torpedo steady, bearing 315. Range: 5,000 yards.

1184
01:57:45,015 --> 01:57:49,019
-再加速  -不行  我们已推动至110%
-Melekhin, more speed.  -Negative. We're already at 110%.

1185
01:57:49,186 --> 01:57:54,816
-那就以115%推进  -估计距离: 300码  快速接近中
-Then give it run at 115%.  -Estimate range: 3,000 yards. Closing awfully fast.

1186
01:58:01,531 --> 01:58:03,043
他想冲向鱼雷...
He's heading right at the torpedo.

1187
01:58:03,043 --> 01:58:04,555
自杀
What's he trying to do, kill himself?

1188
01:58:04,555 --> 01:58:06,067
我们能否
We have a firing solution...

1189
01:58:06,067 --> 01:58:07,579
向苏联雅夫级潜艇开火?
on the Russian alfa. Can we shoot back?

1190
01:58:07,746 --> 01:58:12,501
他们没有向我们开火  我不能擅自向苏联潜艇开火
They didn't shoot at us. I can't attack a Soviet submarine without authorization.

1191
01:58:15,128 --> 01:58:20,717
鱼雷方位315  当前距离: 900码
Torpedo bearing steady at 315. Last range: 900 yards.

1192
01:58:20,884 --> 01:58:25,138
鱼雷20秒后命中
Torpedo impact: 20 seconds.

1193
01:58:26,431 --> 01:58:30,602
-什么书?  -你说什么?
-What books?  -Pardon me?

1194
01:58:30,769 --> 01:58:36,275
-你写过什么书?  -我写过哈尔西上将的传记
-What books did you write?  -A biography on Admiral Halsey...

1195
01:58:36,441 --> 01:58:43,031
-关于海军战斗战略的  -我看过那本书
-called The Fighting Sailor, about naval combat tactics.  -I know this book.

1196
01:58:43,198 --> 01:58:48,078
你的结论错了  哈尔西战术失当
Your conclusions were all wrong, Ryan. Halsey acted stupidly.

1197
01:58:48,245 --> 01:58:53,333
九  八  七  六...
Nine, eight, seven, six...

1198
01:58:53,500 --> 01:58:59,339
五  四  三  二...
five, four, three, two...

1199
01:58:59,506 --> 01:59:02,759
鱼雷现在命中目标
Torpedo impact... now.

1200
01:59:12,102 --> 01:59:15,939
我的天
I'll be dammed.

1201
01:59:16,106 --> 01:59:20,611
-怎么了?  -这是战略
-What happened?  -Combat tactics, Mr. Ryan.

1202
01:59:20,777 --> 01:59:22,825
舰长将射程缩短了
By turning into the torpedo,

1203
01:59:22,877 --> 01:59:26,825
鱼雷来不及引爆
the captain closed the distance before it could arm itself.

1204
01:59:26,992 --> 01:59:29,828
-没事了?  -还不一定
-So that's it?  -Not quite.

1205
01:59:29,995 --> 01:59:33,623
图波列夫舰长会解除武器安全系统
Right now, Captain Tupolev is removing the safety features on all his weapons.

1206
01:59:33,623 --> 01:59:37,252
他不会重蹈覆辙
He won't make the same mistake twice.

1207
01:59:37,419 --> 01:59:42,758
-瓦西里  发炮程式准备好了?  -还没完全准备好...
-Vasily, have you plotted a solution yet?  -It's a little rough, but I...

1208
01:59:49,264 --> 01:59:52,392
-枪声  -听起来好像是的  长官
-Gunfire.  -That's what it sounded like, sir.

1209
01:59:52,559 --> 01:59:56,396
-他不会改变主意?  -是船员作怪
-He won't change his mind, Mr. Ryan.  -It's one of the crew.

1210
01:59:56,563 --> 02:00:00,400
不管他是谁  他有二心
Well, Whoever he is, I'd say he's having second thoughts.

1211
02:00:16,416 --> 02:00:19,836
我想看看蒙大拿
I would like to have seen Montana.

1212
02:00:32,933 --> 02:00:35,957
舰长  他跑进导弹库
Captain, he stumbled forward into the missile bay.

1213
02:00:35,957 --> 02:00:38,981
20号舱响起警报
There's a silo hatch warning... port side, number 20.

1214
02:00:39,147 --> 02:00:43,318
-他不能发射导弹吧?  -不能  但是他能够引爆导弹
-He can't launch a missile?  -No, but he can blow one up.

1215
02:00:45,529 --> 02:00:48,617
舰长  守着指挥台
Captain, take the conn. Fire control's blasted to hell.

1216
02:00:48,629 --> 02:00:50,617
躲在他后面吧
Get in behind him and stay there.

1217
02:00:50,784 --> 02:00:53,495
舰长  慢着
Captain, wait.

1218
02:00:56,164 --> 02:00:59,293
你可能需要这个  舰长
You may need this, sir.

1219
02:01:02,004 --> 02:01:04,298
谢谢
Thank you.

1220
02:01:06,925 --> 02:01:09,907
别光站着  跟着他  拿着家伙过去
Don't just stand there, Ryan, go with him!

1221
02:01:09,907 --> 02:01:11,398
-你会说英语?  -是的
-You, you speak English?  -Yes, sir.

1222
02:01:11,398 --> 02:01:12,889
你也跟着去
get your butt over here.

1223
02:01:13,056 --> 02:01:16,393
舰长  鱼雷未命中
Captain, torpedo broke off on impact.

1224
02:01:16,393 --> 02:01:18,061
妈的  解除鱼雷保险
Goddamn it! Set the safety ranges for zero now.

1225
02:01:18,061 --> 02:01:19,730
舰长  我已经尽快在弄了
Captain, I can't go any faster.

1226
02:01:19,896 --> 02:01:24,443
千万不能让他破坏点火电路
We must get him before he gets to the ignition circuits.

1227
02:01:31,575 --> 02:01:35,120
破坏点火电路会有什么后果?
What happens if he gets to that ignition circuitry?

1228
02:01:35,287 --> 02:01:38,290
他会烧毁整艘潜艇
He can incinerate the ship.

1229
02:01:45,672 --> 02:01:50,344
-这个门是唯一出口?  -是的
-That door is the only way out of here?  -Yes.

1230
02:01:50,510 --> 02:01:55,682
-别让他跑掉  -瑞恩...
-Don't let him get past you.  -Ryan...

1231
02:01:55,849 --> 02:01:59,227
小心开枪
Be careful what you shoot at.

1232
02:01:59,394 --> 02:02:04,232
这里有很多东西不能中弹
Most things in here don't react too well to bullets.

1233
02:02:06,109 --> 02:02:08,737
对
Right.

1234
02:02:26,046 --> 02:02:28,966
你不知道小心开枪吗?
Be careful what I shoot at?

1235
02:02:37,224 --> 02:02:41,311
-鱼雷保险解除了  - 声纳  红十月号在哪里?
-Safety ranges set to zero.  -Sonar, give me the bearing for Red October.

1236
02:02:41,478 --> 02:02:47,192
-它在我们后面  -右满舵  我要打败他
-She's taking positioned behind us.  -Right full rudder. I'll shake the man loose.

1237
02:02:53,407 --> 02:02:57,077
-它在下潜  -俯倾30度
-He's going deep.  -30 degree down angle.

1238
02:02:57,244 --> 02:02:59,913
反鱼雷在那边? 很好
All the countermeasures were over there, right? Very well.

1239
02:03:25,355 --> 02:03:29,401
司令  雅夫级潜艇太快  他们逃不掉的
Admiral, the alfa's too quick. It's only a matter of time on search.

1240
02:03:29,568 --> 02:03:34,656
"瑞恩  这里有很多东西不能中弹..."
"Ryan, some things in here don't react well to bullets..."

1241
02:03:34,823 --> 02:03:38,619
对  我也不能中弹
Yeah, like me. I don't react well to bullets.

1242
02:03:58,221 --> 02:04:01,433
-钟斯  他在哪里?  -距离很近
-Where is he, Jonesy?  -Close, sir.

1243
02:04:03,352 --> 02:04:06,855
-正前方900米  -终于找到了
-900 meters, directly ahead.  -Got him.

1244
02:04:07,022 --> 02:04:10,192
-校准后发射  -距离太近
-Mark bearings and fire.  -We are too close.

1245
02:04:10,359 --> 02:04:15,739
别争论  发射鱼雷
Don't argue with me. Do it now!

1246
02:04:17,240 --> 02:04:20,702
又发射了一颗鱼雷  它随时会爆炸
Another torpedo. It went active the moment it was launched.

1247
02:04:20,869 --> 02:04:25,666
-左满舵  平衡舰首  -鱼雷锁定我们了
-Left full rudder. Ease off on your bow planes.  -I think he's got us.

1248
02:04:35,592 --> 02:04:39,012
达拉斯号  干得漂亮!
Way to go, Dallas!

1249
02:04:42,766 --> 02:04:47,896
鱼雷在五百码外冲过来  你成功了
Torpedo is in acquisition. Range 500 yards and closing. You've done it, Thompson!

1250
02:04:48,063 --> 02:04:52,359
希望这行得通  大副  浮上水面
I hope this works. All right, chief, put us on the roof.

1251
02:04:52,526 --> 02:04:55,988
准备发射反鱼雷  听我命令  五  四...
Countermeasure station, on my mark. 5, 4...

1252
02:04:58,699 --> 02:05:03,829
发射反鱼雷  紧急上浮
Release counter measures. Emergency blow. Full rise.

1253
02:05:11,003 --> 02:05:14,590
500英尺
500 feet.

1254
02:05:14,756 --> 02:05:18,176
快点上浮
Come on, Big D. Fly!

1255
02:05:37,029 --> 02:05:40,699
鱼雷没停下来  它在寻找别的目标
That torpedo is still active. It's searching for another target, now.

1256
02:06:05,933 --> 02:06:11,146
竟然是他X的厨师
A goddamn cook.

1257
02:06:33,961 --> 02:06:37,089
它锁定我们了!
Torpedo is locked on us!

1258
02:06:37,256 --> 02:06:40,050
-雅夫级潜艇离我们多近?  -左后方1000码处
-How close is that Alfa, Jonesy?  -1,000 yards dead astern, going to port.

1259
02:06:40,050 --> 02:06:42,844
-反方向转  -遵命
-Reverse your turn.  -Aye,sir.

1260
02:06:48,308 --> 02:06:52,562
我们冲向敌方  鱼雷跟着我们
We're turning straight at him. Torpedo's still on our tail.

1261
02:06:56,441 --> 02:07:01,238
在适当的时候退开
The hard part about playing chicken is knowing when to flinch.

1262
02:07:06,618 --> 02:07:10,664
距离400码  350码  300码...
Collision in 400 yards, 350, 300...

1263
02:07:10,831 --> 02:07:16,545
-舰长!  -右满舵  俯倾30度
-Captain!  -Right full rudder. 30 degree down angle.

1264
02:07:16,712 --> 02:07:20,173
这次必定很惊险
This one's going to be close.

1265
02:07:23,093 --> 02:07:26,847
你个傲慢的傻瓜  你会害死我们
You arrogant ass, you've killed us.

1266
02:07:55,208 --> 02:07:58,337
我们确定了红十月号的位置
We have ascertained the Red October's final position.

1267
02:07:58,964 --> 02:08:01,924
但爆炸碎片
But...given the depth of the water and the spread of...

1268
02:08:01,924 --> 02:08:04,885
遍布深海
the wreckage spreads across a wide area...

1269
02:08:05,052 --> 02:08:07,971
我们要花一段时间调查
it'll be some time before anything's recovered.

1270
02:08:08,138 --> 02:08:10,953
你们的人正在
However, your people are interviewing...

1271
02:08:10,953 --> 02:08:13,769
安排船员回国
the crew now and making arrangements for their return.

1272
02:08:13,936 --> 02:08:18,273
这是一场悲惨的意外  大使先生
This has been a terrible tragedy, Mr. Ambassador.

1273
02:08:18,440 --> 02:08:23,695
如果早点找我们  悲剧可能不会发生
And I can only stress hat if you'd come to us earlier, it might have been avoided.

1274
02:08:24,780 --> 02:08:30,702
-我欣赏你坦诚的性格  -彼此彼此
-I appreciate your candor in the matter.  -And I yours, Andrei.

1275
02:08:33,455 --> 02:08:36,291
可能在将来
Perhaps in the future...

1276
02:08:36,291 --> 02:08:39,127
会有更先进的科技来研究潜艇残骸
the technology will be available for an investigation of the wreckage.

1277
02:08:39,294 --> 02:08:43,173
也许吧
Perhaps.

1278
02:08:47,469 --> 02:08:53,850
-还有一件事  我难以启齿...  -请说
-There is another matter, one that I'm reluctant to...  -Please.

1279
02:08:55,352 --> 02:09:02,442
一艘雅夫级潜艇  曾经在大浅滩出没
One of our submarines, an Alfa, was last reported in the area of the Grand Banks.

1280
02:09:02,609 --> 02:09:06,863
它跟我们失去联络
We've not heard from her for some time.

1281
02:09:08,156 --> 02:09:12,703
又一艘潜艇失踪?
Andrei. You've lost another submarine?

1282
02:09:20,103 --> 02:09:24,503
缅因州  佩诺布斯科特河

1283
02:09:27,092 --> 02:09:31,597
长途跋涉来  把潜艇藏在河里
All this way to hide a submarine in a river.

1284
02:09:32,806 --> 02:09:35,871
这儿距离海军基地一百英里
We're 100 miles from the nearest naval base...

1285
02:09:35,871 --> 02:09:38,937
而且卫星不会再窥探这地方
for the last place that satellites will ever look.

1286
02:09:40,439 --> 02:09:44,318
我在这里长大
I grew up around here.

1287
02:09:44,484 --> 02:09:49,823
祖父在那个岛教我钓鱼
My grandfather taught me to fish off that island over there.

1288
02:09:52,868 --> 02:09:59,833
你心里还有一个疑问  为什么不问?
There is one question you haven't asked me yet. Why?

1289
02:10:01,627 --> 02:10:04,963
在适当的时候  你自然会说出来
Well, I figured you would tell me when you were ready.

1290
02:10:07,883 --> 02:10:12,512
有人说  我们要主动攻打美国
Now, there are those who believe we should attack the United States first.

1291
02:10:12,679 --> 02:10:19,186
了却一切恩怨  红十月号就是为此而建造的
Settle everything in one moment. Red October was built for that purpose.

1292
02:10:19,353 --> 02:10:24,900
-然后  莫斯科会付出沉重的代价  -也许吧
-When the dust settles from this, there's going to be hell to pay in Moscow.

1293
02:10:25,067 --> 02:10:28,278
那可能是好事
Maybe some good will come from it.

1294
02:10:28,445 --> 02:10:34,117
一场小革命能整顿国家  你觉得呢?
A little revolution now and then is a healthy thing, do you think?

1295
02:10:39,915 --> 02:10:43,710
-你仍然喜欢钓鱼吗  瑞恩?  -是的
-Do you still like to fish, Ryan?  -Mmm.

1296
02:10:45,128 --> 02:10:49,049
维尔纳斯有一条河  跟这里差不多
There's a river, not unlike this one, near Vilnius...

1297
02:10:49,216 --> 02:10:53,887
我祖父在那里教我钓鱼
where my grandfather taught me to fish.

1298
02:10:54,930 --> 02:10:59,685
"大海为每个人带来新希望"
"And the sea will grant each man new hope."

1299
02:10:59,851 --> 02:11:03,563
"正如睡眠带来梦境"
"As sleep brings dreams."

1300
02:11:09,611 --> 02:11:12,322
克里斯托弗  哥伦布
Christopher Columbus.

1301
02:11:16,201 --> 02:11:19,580
欢迎光临新世界  舰长
Welcome to the new world, sir.


